Mint SA engages in the provision of telecommunication and energy consumption services. The company is headquartered in Montpellier, Occitanie and currently employs 27 full-time employees. The firm's offerings include the No Limit package, which enables residential customers to make unlimited fixed-line telephone calls for a fixed monthly tariff, the Budget Mobile package, which enables customers to send messages (SMS) and make discounted mobile telephone calls for a fixed monthly tariff, and the fixed-line telephone package, whereby customers just pay for the calls they make. The firm also provides international telephony services, aimed at both foreign nationals living in France, and French citizens living overseas, as well as in Italy, Belgium and Spain; voice-over Internet protocol (VoIP) services, and Internet services. Budget Telecom provides its services to both private and business customers. The company controlled as of December 31, 2011, one subsidiary, Kast Online SARL. In February 2014, it acquired Effineo.

Eurasia Groupe SA engages in the real estate activities. The company is headquartered in Gennevilliers, Ile-De-France and currently employs 15 full-time employees. The company has three types of activities: direct renting, which consists of acquisition of shops and show-rooms, warehouses and offices in order to rent them; subleasing, which includes leasing of shops and show-rooms, warehouses and offices in order to sublease them, and hotel activities, which comprise managing of one own 43 room hotel. The firm operates through its subsidiaries.

Artea SA, formerly Medea SA is a France-based company engaged in the design, production, and marketing of anti-skid tire studs. The Company's activity is organized into three areas: Sale of studs, intended for touring vehicles, light trucks, heavy trucks, heavy equipment, and competitive vehicles; Sales of stud-insertion equipment for semi-automatic machines, guns, spare parts, among others and Services. As of December 31, 2011, Medea was 96.70%-owned by Metrovacesa SA.

Advicenne SA develops and markets pediatric drugs for the treatment of neurological diseases. The company is headquartered in Nimes, Occitanie and currently employs 26 full-time employees. The firm focuses on the development of paediatric friendly therapeutics for the treatment of orphan renal diseases and niche neurology indications. The Company’s medicines are developed for patients of all ages in the fields of nephrology and neurology. Its lead product includes ADV7103, which is in phase III, designed to address dRTA both in children for whom the disease is genetic as well as for adults who may have acquired the condition as a result of autoimmune disease. Apart from its lead product, the Company also develops a portfolio of products, including ADV6209, which is an oral liquid solution for moderate sedation; Likozam, which is designed to meet the unmet medical need of patients with partial and generalized chronic refractory epilepsy; Levidcen, which is used to address the unmet medical need of epileptic patients with partial onset seizures, and ADV7103 Cystinuria, among others.

Theranexus SA engages in the design and development of drug candidates affecting the interaction between neurons and glial cells. The company is headquartered in Lyon, Auvergne-Rhone-Alpes and currently employs 16 full-time employees. The firm is a biopharmaceutical entity that develops drug candidates to be used in the treatment of central nervous system (CNS) disorders, including epilepsy, narcolepsy, Parkinson's disease, Alzheimer's disease, neuropathic pain and psychiatric disorders. Its patented technology is aimed at increasing the efficacy of CNS drugs, which are approved and available on the market. The firm's technology is protected, scalable and versatile, and used to generate high value-added proprietary drug candidates for different conditions, while reducing time-to-market and market entry costs and risks in comparison with standard drug development processes. Theranexus SA operates in the domestic market.

Adocia SA is a clinical-stage biotechnology company, which engages in the development of medicines from already-approved therapeutic proteins and peptides. The company is headquartered in Lyon, Auvergne-Rhone-Alpes and currently employs 138 full-time employees. The company specializes in the research and development of biotherapy products used in tissue regeneration and for treating chronic diseases. The firm develops a BioChaperone Platform used for therapeutic protein delivery in regenerative medicine and chronic disease areas, such as wound Healing, diabetes, ulcers and monoclonal antibody creation. The firm completed two Phases I and II studies of the formulation of human insulin, two Phases I and II studies of insulin lispro and one Phase I/II on a combination of insulin glargine, the basal insulin and insulin lispro, an insulin analog. Adocia also undertaken the activities in the field of formulation of monoclonal antibodies which are molecules for the treatment of various chronic pathologies (oncology, inflammation, etc. ).

Auplata Mining Group SA is a gold mining exploration and operation company. The company is headquartered in Remire Montjoly, Guyane and currently employs 8 full-time employees. The firm operates three gold mines in French Guiana: Dieu Merci, which is near the village of Saint-Elie, west of Cayenne, with three permits held by the Company, including Dieu Merci, Victory and Renaissance; Yaou, which is located north east of the town of Maripasoula, with an operation permit and operation authorization held by the Company, Yaou EA and Dorlin, which is located in the centre west region of French Guiana, with an operation permit EA. The firm has also research permits in the Bon Espoir gold mine and the Iracoubo Sud gold mine.

ADLPartner SA engages in public relations and marketing services. The company is headquartered in Chantilly, Hauts-De-France and currently employs 376 full-time employees. The firm designs, markets and implements customer relations loyalty and management services on its own behalf or on behalf of its partners. ADLPartner SA devises open-ended subscriptions (OES), which is a formula that helps recruiting subscribers using a direct-debit system; fixed-term subscriptions (FTS), which relates to the recruitment of subscribers for a fixed-term, usually one year, and books-items-audio-video (BIAV). The firm's principal clients are: banks, such as BNP Paribas; distribution companies, such as Printemps; service providers, including Amercan Express, and companies engaged in distant selling, such as La Redoute. The company operates in Germany, Spain and Brazil. The company has several wholly owned subsidiaries, including SCI de la Rue de Chartres and ADLPartner Hispania, among others. In September 2014, the Company launched its subsidiary ADLP Digital.

Delfingen Industry SA engages in the provision of automobile equipment. The company is headquartered in Anteuil, Bourgogne-Franche-Comte and currently employs 2,527 full-time employees. In the automotive sector it offers a range of products, mainly comprised of plastics, that aim at protecting, fastening and ensuring the routing of automotive wiring harnesses; in the building and housing sector it develops and sells appliances and special applications and glass protection, and in the electrical equipment sector it offers products suited for the electrical equipment market insuring cable insulation for transformers, motors, generators and multiple electrical equipment. The company is present in Brazil, China, Honduras, India, Italy, Korea, Mexico, Morocco, Philippines, Portugal, Romania, Slovakia, Tunisia, Turkey and the United States. The company operates through Kartar Wire Industries Pvt Ltd, a provider of plastic extruded tubing and Drossbach North America Inc.

AST Groupe engages in construction and real-estate development activities. The company is headquartered in Decines-Charpieu, Auvergne-Rhone-Alpes and currently employs 691 full-time employees. The firm acts as project manager and specializes in coordinating construction and promotion of individual houses situated in various regions of France, such as Rhone-Alpes, Bourgogne, Franche-Comte, Provence, Languedoc-Roussillon, Midi-Pyrenees and Ile de France. In addition, the Company is involved in land development, as well as the purchase of land and its division into plots, rendering them viable for building. As of December 31, 2011, the Company operated through wholly owned subsidiaries, such as Evolim, AST Services, Pobi Structures SARL, Pobi Charpentes SA and Microsit SA, among others. In June 2014, its affliate, AST Fund Solutions, LLC, has completed acquisition of D.F. King & Co., Inc. (D.F. King) and its operating businesses and Donlin, Recano & Company, Inc. (Donlin Recano).

WE.CONNECT SA designs, manufactures and distributes computer products and equipment to professionals and peripheral technology under its brands each adapted to a particular type of customer. The company is headquartered in Paris, Ile-De-France and currently employs 33 full-time employees. Connect SA is a French-based importer and distributor of photographic, audiovisual and cinema equipment. The firm provides digital cameras, memory cards, storage systems, scanners, non-digital cameras, cinema equipment, professional video and surveillance equipment and professional photography equipment, as well as several brands of video projectors, slide projectors and projection screens, among others. The Company’s clients are chain, Internet and specialized stores, including Auchan, Wacon, Rue du Commerce, Pixmania, Carrefour Hypermarches, Signal and Leclerc, among others. The company operates through its subsidiary Techni Cine Phot SAS, Pca France and Halterrego.

Ambow Education Holding Ltd. engages in the provision of educational and career enhancement services. The company is headquartered in Beijing, Beijing and currently employs 1,694 full-time employees. The firm offers individualized services and products through its combined online and offline delivery model. The company has two business divisions: Better Schools and Better Jobs. The company operates through three operating segments, which are tutoring, K-12 schools and career enhancement. Its tutoring and K-12 schools segments are within its Better Schools division and career enhancement segment is within its Better Jobs division. The company has over 50 learning centers and schools, comprising over 20 tutoring centers, four K-12 schools, 10 career enhancement centers, 20 training offices and one career enhancement campus, which are located in over 20 provinces and autonomous regions within China. Its educational services cover K-12 programs and tutoring services, which provide test preparation programs. Its Better Schools division consists of over 20 tutoring centers and over four K-12 schools.

Accord Financial Corp. is a holding company, which engages in the provision of asset-based financial services to industrial and commercial enterprises. The company is headquartered in Westmount, Quebec and currently employs 104 full-time employees. The firm's business involves ABL by Accord Financial Inc. and Accord Financial, Inc., which entails financing or purchasing receivables on a recourse basis, as well as financing other tangible assets, such as inventory and equipment; lease financing and equipment and working capital lending by Accord Equipment Finance, and credit protection and receivables management services by Accord Financial Ltd., which involves providing credit guarantees and collection services, generally without financing. Its clients operate in various industries, including apparel, financial and professional services, manufacturing, wholesale and distribution, transportation, chemicals, electronics, oilfield services and textiles.

Actia Group engages in the electronic equipment for buoyant vehicle and telecommunications markets. The company is headquartered in Toulouse, Occitanie and currently employs 3,697 full-time employees. The firm has two divisions, the Automotive Division, engaged in the design and distribution of electronic diagnostics systems for cars and trucks and vehicle testing equipment, the design and distribution of onboard electronics for industrial and military vehicles, as well as the development of complex electronic systems, and the Telecom Division, principally involved in the production of signal transmission and reception equipment, information transmission products and ground stations systems. The Company’s clients include Volvo, Somfy, Thales, Siemes, Airbus, France Telecom, Boeing, Media Broadcast and AFP, among others. As of December 31, 2013, Actia Group operated through offices located in the USA, Poland and China, among others. The firm also operates through several subsidiaries, including Actia Automotive, Mors Inc, Ardia and SCI Oratoire, among others.

Aurea SA is a holding company, which engages in the recycling business. The company is headquartered in Paris, Ile-De-France and currently employs 551 full-time employees. The firm focuses on activities related to the recycling of motor oils, to the production of wheels with solid rubber tires at the base of used tires, and to the recycling of polyvinyl chloride (PVC). Aurea operates through its direct and indirect subsidiaries, including Compagnie Francaise Eco Huile SA, which is engaged in the recycling of oils used in vehicle motors; Rulo NV, which is involved in PVC recycling; Flaurea Chemicals SA, which provides hazardous waste treatment; DB Energies, which supplies petroleum products for heating, roads vehicles, agricultural tractors and public works machinery, and Roll Gom SAS that specializes in the treatment of used tires and Hipcricket, among others.

1000mercis SA engages in the provision of interactive advertising and marketing solutions. The company is headquartered in Paris, Ile-De-France and currently employs 399 full-time employees. The firm creates conquest and loyalty marketing solutions for businesses through interactive marketing and publicity and through mobile marketing. The company provides services through inactive media, such as Internet, mobile phones, among others. The company provides database analysis with knowledge of online statistical models and a test and learns approach. The firm also pursues expertise in the field of online database conception, development and exploitation. Its clients are YAHOO!, Easyjet.com, Meetic, Accor, ebookers, Tagheuer, Adidas, BNP Paribas, among others. The firm operates through subsidiaries Ocito, based in Paris and 1000mercis Ltd, based in London.

Hybrigenics SA operates as a biopharmaceutical company which engages in the research and development of targets and therapies for the treatment of proliferative diseases. The company is headquartered in Paris, Ile-De-France and currently employs 17 full-time employees. The company specializes in the research and development of drugs intended for cancer treatment and supplies scientific services in the protein interaction field. The firm is specialized in the research and development (R&D) of drugs to fight cancer. The company is organized in two units: Hybrigenics Pharma for internal R&D, which develops a research program aimed at such diseases as melanoma and prostate cancer; and Hybrigenics Services for commercial business, mainly engaged in protein interaction information and solutions. Hybrigenics SA’s main development program is based on inecalcitol, a vitamin D analogue, for prostate cancer treatment. The company operates through Hybrigenics Corporation and Imaxio.

Valbiotis SA develops products and candidate drugs designed to prevent metabolic diseases. The company is headquartered in Perigny, Nouvelle-Aquitaine and currently employs 35 full-time employees. The firm specializes in developing nutrition solutions designed to prevent cardiometabolic diseases and provide nutritional support for patients. The company seeks to develop solutions designed to prevent type 2 diabetes, NASH, (non-alcoholic steatohepatitis) and obesity and to offer nutritional support. The firm prevents disease by developing products that reduce the risk factors of irreversible chronic diseases. The company provides patient support through new-generation medical nutrition solutions containing patented substances with clinically proven effects. Its products are plant-based and undergo strict scientific and clinical tests in collaboration with academic research centers.

Bilendi SA engages in the design and marketing of internet customer reward programs. The company is headquartered in Paris, Ile-De-France and currently employs 234 full-time employees. The firm provides services for both individual Internet users and companies with online shopping facilities. The company is split into four principal divisions: Maximiles TM, Maximiles Loyalty Services, Maximails Panels and Maximail. Maximiles.com operates the Internet loyalty scheme. Maximiles Loyalty Services solutions include proprietary customer loyalty programs, channel and sales promotion incentives and database management. Maximiles Panels provides survey sampling and panel recruitment and incentives services. Maximail uses member purchasing history, demographic and lifestyle data in order to deliver e-mail marketing campaigns. The firm is present in France, the United Kingdom, Belgium, Spain and Italy. The company also operates several subsidiaries, including Elma, Dateos, Fabuleos, 2WLS and M3 Research, among others.

Aquila Resources, Inc. engages in the exploration, acquisition, and development of mineral properties. The company is headquartered in Toronto, Ontario. The firm operates through the acquisition and exploration of precious metals projects segment. The primary asset of the Company is its interest in the Back Forty Project located in Menominee County, Michigan. The Back Forty Project is a development-stage volcanogenic massive sulfide (VMS) deposit containing gold, zinc, lead, silver and copper located in the Upper Peninsula of Michigan, the United States. Back Forty Project is a poly-metallic project, which contains approximately one million ounces of gold and one billion pounds of zinc. Its two other exploration projects include Reef Gold Project (Reef) located in Marathon County Wisconsin, and the Bend Project (Bend) located in Taylor County, Wisconsin. Reef is a gold copper property and Bend is a volcanogenic massive sulfide occurrence containing copper and gold. At Reef Project, the Company has completed over 42 diamond drill holes.

Ediliziacrobatica SpA is an Italy-based company specialized in acrobatic services for the construction industry working without scaffolding but only using ropes. It offers a wide range of services divided in six categories: Cleaning, Refurbishment, Placement, Complete and Partial Renovation, First Aid and Securing, and Special. The Cleaning offering includes cleaning services of chimneys, drainpipes and glass walls, among others. The Refurbishment offering includes maintenance services for facades, massive walls and solar panels, among others. The Placement offering includes placement services of chimneys, advertising panels and anti-pigeon systems, among others. Complete and Partial Renovation offers renovation services for the building exterior parts. First Aid and Securing offers services for secure buildings in case of emergency, such as after a natural disaster. Special offers extraordinary maintenance services.

Ecoslops SA engages in the development and implementation of technology to produce fuel and light bitumen from oil residue. The company is headquartered in Paris, Ile-De-France and currently employs 52 full-time employees. The firm offers seaports, residues collectors, ship-owners and bunker suppliers with a technology to recycle oily waste of ships. Ecoslops SA is active in promoting the development of the P2R unit by its incorporation in a more global plant: Oil Waste Processing Plant (OW2P). The OW2P technology combines a refining petroleum process (P2R) with appropriate clean water. The firm recycles the waste in order to be used in electricity production and steam production among others. The firm's fuel production is located in the port of Sines, Portugal.

DRONE VOLT SA engages in the design, assembly and marketing of remote controlled terrestrial and aerial drones for the media, security and surveillance, transportation, agriculture, and topography sectors. The company is headquartered in Villepinte, Ile-De-France and currently employs 57 full-time employees. The firm provides civilian drone manufacturing. The company specializes in the production, integration and sale of drones for professionals. Drone Volt is a provider of the audiovisual market in the field of aerial photography by drone. The firm is also present in many other markets such as security and topography, among others. The firm's main product is the Pack PRO FOR GH4 S900. The company cooperates with Ministry of Internal Affaires, Ministry of Defense, CERN, Gendarmerie Transports Aeriens (aerial transport police), Dakar 2015, Spie, TF1, Bouygues, CNRS, Bonne Pioche, RAID and GEDEON Programmes, among others. The company operates through Dandrone.

AudioValley SA provides audio and visual production services. The company is headquartered in Bruxelles, Bruxelles-Capitale. The firm offers services ranging from monetization of digital radio, licensing, in-store digital audio commercialization to the creation, streaming and hosting of online radio. Its product portfolio includes Radionomy, which is a free platform that enables users from around the world to create their own digital radio on the Internet and FM radios, as well as provides tools to broadcast, promote and monetize their radio; Storever, which is an international agency offering in store solutions for brands covering music services, digital signage, interactive solutions and audiovisual equipment for retail players, and Jamendo, which is an independent global music community that supports independent artists by licensing their musical works for commercial use, among others. The firm is also present in France, the United states, Germany, Spain, China and Luxembourg.

Altisource Asset Management Corp. engages in the provision of portfolio management and governance services to investment vehicles that acquire and own residential properties. The company employs 103 full-time employees The firm's primary client is Altisource Residential Corporation (Residential). The firm operates through segment, which is focused on providing asset management and certain corporate governance services to Residential. Its business strategy is to provide asset management services to Residential to generate cash available for distribution to its shareholders and thereby growing its earnings, and develop additional investment strategies and vehicles. Residential is a public real estate investment trust (REIT) that acquires and manages single-family rental properties by acquiring sub-performing and non-performing mortgage loans throughout the United States. In addition to providing services to Residential, it also provides management services to NewSource Reinsurance Company Ltd., which is an insurance and reinsurance company.

Azarga Uranium Corp. engages in the exploration and development of uranium. The company is headquartered in Greenwood Village, Colorado and currently employs 11 full-time employees. The firm controls uranium properties located in the United States of America and in the Kyrgyz Republic. The company operates through two segments: the Kyrgyzstan Uranium Division and the United States Uranium Division. Its Dewey Burdock Project, located in South Dakota, is its initial development priority. The project is an in-situ recovery uranium project located in the Edgemont uranium district, in South Dakota, the United States. The company also owns the Centennial Project, the Aladdin Deposit in Wyoming, over two uranium exploration properties in Wyoming and the Kyzyl Ompul Project. The Centennial Project is located in the western part of Weld County in northeastern Colorado. The Aladdin Deposit consists of approximately 6,810 acres of mineral rights. The uranium deposit/prospects of the Kyzyl Ompul Project are located in the Kyrgyz Republic.

Emakina Group SA engages in the provision of website designs, developing services, and related services. The company is headquartered in Watermael-Boitsfort, Bruxelles-Capitale and currently employs 413 full-time employees. All activities of the Company is split into several divisions: Integrated, Interactive, Web building, Applications, Strategy, Architects, Media, Direct, Perform, Social, Motion, Mobile and Operations. The company mainly designs and builds websites to communicate about organizations, presents services and product range and target audiences, creates mini-sites and rich media brand sites, banner and rich media campaigns including landing pages for conversion, provides solution building and technical architecture, testing and release management, development and project management and agency, provides holistic brand keeping, brand, design and campaign concept and guidelines services. The firm is present in Belgium, France and the Netherlands. The company operates through Relephant, Karbyn and Doe Blomberg Gottberg.

Poujoulat SA engages in the manufacture and marketing of chimney flues and metal roof outlets. The company is headquartered in St-Symphorien, Nouvelle-Aquitaine and currently employs 1,436 full-time employees. The firm's range of products includes metal chimneys, flue liners and connections for heating apparatus, chimney tops, ventilation pipes and accessories. In addition, it offers installation services and contract management. The company produces individual, collective or industrial chimney systems. Poujoulat SA is comprised of companies and branches in seven European countries, including France, Belgium, the Netherlands, Italy, the United Kingdom, Turkey and Poland. The firm operates through Dansk Shorstens Teknik (DST).

Prodware SA is engages in the provision of business solutions. The company is headquartered in Paris, Ile-De-France and currently employs 1,355 full-time employees. The services provided by the Company include enterprise resource planning (ERP) and customer relationship management (CRM) solutions, business solutions, business intelligence tools, as well as networks, security and telecommunication solutions. The company operates through its subsidiaries, such as Prodware Belgium SA, Prodware Luxembourg, RentaSoft and Prodware Tunisie, maXimum ERP, Qurius Spain and Qurius Belgium, among others. The firm formed partnerships with AxPact, Watermark/Qurius Global Alliance, Dell, Microsoft Dynamics, Orange Business Services, Cisco Systems and other. In July, 2013, the Company transferred its non strategic activities of sale and integration of PTC software solutions to 4CAD GROUP, which is a French company whose business activity is focused on PTC solutions integration.

NSE SA designs, manufactures, and distributes electronic equipment and integrated systems. The company is headquartered in Nizerolles, Auvergne-Rhone-Alpes and currently employs 612 full-time employees. The firm's activities are organized around six divisions: Night Vision Systems, including night vision goggles, NVG compatible lights and cockpit modifications; Usage Monitoring Systems (UMS), such as the Brite Saver; satellite communication systems and software; On Board Equipment, including platforms for airborne applications, power converters, airborne phones and avionic control panels; Maintenance Services and management of obsolescence and negotiation services; Satellites Communication Systems and Railway Signals and Systems. The firm has eight facilities in France: Emerainville, Maillane, Taverny, Brive, Bayo, Toulon, Soyons and e-Track systems. ECT Industries SA's wholly owned subsidiaries include Bayo SAS and e-Track systems.

Vogo SA develops sports mobile technology products. The company is headquartered in Montpellier, Occitanie and currently employs 18 full-time employees. The firm develops, markets and distributes a solution for live broadcasting of audiovisual content based on a video stream processing technology. The Company’s solution aims to improve the audience experience through multi-camera content upon-request while providing audio and video analysis tools for fans and professionals. The firm launches VOGO SPORT, which allows spectators within a sport venue or an outdoor event to access live audiovisual content through a mobile or tablet application. Its solution has a number of features, including spectators, which allows users to access instantly and in real time via Smartphone, tablets or computers, as well as services, such as, replay, zoom and slow motion.

Air Industries Group is an aerospace company, which engages in the manufacture and design of structural parts and assemblies that focus on flight safety, including landing gear, arresting gear, engine mounts, flight controls, throttle quadrants, jet engines, and other components. The company is headquartered in Bay Shore, New York and currently employs 209 full-time employees. The firm manufactures and designs structural parts and assemblies that focus on flight safety, including landing gear, arresting gear, engine mounts, flight controls, throttle quadrants, jet engines and other components. The firm operates in three segments: Complex Machining, Aerostructures and Electronics and Turbine Engine Components. The Complex Machining segment consists of Air Industries Machining, Corp. and Nassau Tool Works, Inc. The Aerostructures and Electronics segment consists of Woodbine Products, Inc., Miller Stuart, Inc., Eur-Pac Corporation, Electronic Connection Corporation and Compac Development Corporation. The Turbine Engine Components segment consists of AMK Welding, Inc. and The Sterling Engineering Corporation, which makes components for jet engines and ground turbines. The firm also provides sheet metal fabrication of aerostructures, tube bending and welding services.

Acerus Pharmaceuticals Corp. engages in the development, manufacture, production, marketing, and distribution of women's and men's health products. The company is headquartered in Mississauga, Ontario and currently employs 29 full-time employees. The firm is engaged in the development, manufacture, marketing and distribution of products with a focus on men's health, including urology, and women's health, including hormone replacement therapy and female sexual dysfunction. The firm markets Estrace in Canada, which is an oral, plant-derived 17-beta estradiol therapy for the relief of symptoms of menopause. The firm offers Natesto, which is the testosterone nasal gel in the United States for replacement therapy in adult males for conditions associated with a deficiency or absence of endogenous testosterone (hypogonadism). The firm offers TEFINA, which is a low-dose nasal testosterone gel treatment in development for female sexual dysfunction. The firm focuses on TriVair Deposition/Dispersion System, which is a unit dose dry powder inhaler and nasal dispersion system.

Annovis Bio, Inc. is a clinical stage, drug platform company. The Company is focused on addressing neurodegeneration, such as Alzheimer's disease in Down syndrome (AD-DS), Alzheimer's disease (AD) and Parkinson's disease (PD). The Company is engaged in developing drugs that normalize the transport of information within and between nerve cells, called axonal transport. Its lead product pipelines are ANVS-401, which include ANVS-401 for AD, ANVS-401 for AD-DS, ANVS-401 for PD; ANVS-405 and ANVS-301. Its ANVS-401 restores axonal transport and homeostasis in the brain by inhibiting the synthesis of neurotoxic proteins. The Company is in an ongoing Phase II A proof-of-concept study in mild to moderate AD patients and a ready program to conduct a second Phase II A study in PD patients. The Company has also developed compound to treat acute neurodegeneration traumatic brain injury (TBI) and stroke.

Le Tanneur et Cie SA engages in the manufacture, design, and distribution of leather products. The company is headquartered in Paris, Ile-De-France and currently employs 657 full-time employees. The company offers collections of billfolds, handbags, briefcases, luggage and various accessories. The firm creates, manufactures and markets its products under the following brand names: Le Tanneur and Soco. The firm's retail network under the brand Le Tanneur is comprised of stores in France, Belgium and Luxembourg. The company also distributes its products online, through the www.letanneur.com Website. In addition, the Company manufactures products for brands at its production site of Bort-les-Orgues. The firm's subsidiaries are Le Tanneur & Cie Bruxelles SA, Sopadima Far-East, Le Tanneur Chine Co Ltd, Le Tanneur Japan KK, Maroquinerie des Orgues and Somacap.

Witbe SA develops business and metrics monitoring software solutions. The company is headquartered in Paris, Ile-De-France and currently employs 93 full-time employees. The firm offers a wide range of services from monitoring, to complete 24/7 administration, including diagnosis and resolution of malfunctions to help enterprises and service providers keep their commitments to their users. The firm provides the real-time information on the Quality of Experience delivered on any type of platform (enterprise application, Website, Internet Protocol television (IPTV) servers, among others) of user's device (computer, smartphone, mobile phone, tablet, among others) and over any type of network (fixed, mobile, among others). The firm has its offices in Paris, New York, Montreal and Singapore.

Tronic's Microsystems SA designs and manufactures micro electro mechanical systems. The company is headquartered in Crolles, Auvergne-Rhone-Alpes and currently employs 88 full-time employees. The firm is the supplier of such MEMS as accelerometers and gyros with special metals, DRIE, wafer level packaging, nano-imprint, glass processing and SOI, among others. The firm is also specialized in the silicon surface and ratio micromachining, as well as in MEMS ASIC interface design management. The firm offers MEMS devices in many different applications including: BioMEMS, high performance inertial MEMS, RF MEMS swtiches, micromirrors, thermal printheads and MEMS for medical devices, among others. The firm has wafer factories in Europe and the United States, the Company is a spin-off from LETI. Its main shareholder is EPCOS AG.

Baikowski SASU is a France-based company specialized in specialty inorganics. The Company focuses on purity alumina powders & formulations, as well as other oxides & composites, such as spinel and ceria. Its product portfolio includes special oxides, such as yttria stabilized zirconia, magnesia, and mixed oxides, which includes magnesium aluminate spinels, yttrium aluminum garnets, and zirconia toughened alumina; baikalox regular, which provides customers with services regarding alumina powders throughout the production process; polishing suspensions, which provides polishing solutions for a wide variety of substrates; baikalox b-series, especially developed for specialty ceramics, ultraviolet (UV)-reflective. coatings and precision polishing applications, and baikalox high density, which is developed for sapphire applications, among others.

Hiolle Industries engages in the provision of environmental and industrial services. The company is headquartered in Prouvy, Hauts-De-France and currently employs 837 full-time employees. The firm has four divisions: Industrial Services and Environment, Energies, Railways and Transport, and Others. The Industrial Services and Environment division is engaged in the manufacture of products in plastic industry, metal construction and foundry and maintenance, among others and specializes in the design and manufacture of equipment for waste treatment for waste such as derelict cars, scrap and non-hazardous industrial waste; the installation of equipment for smoke treatment, and the engineering of water treatment, among others. Through the Railways and Transports division Hiolle is involved technical installations and wiring works, among others. Through its Renewable Energies it plans, installs and services photovoltaic power plants. Hiolle Industries also offers water treatment consulting and engineering services.

Sapmer SA operates as a fishing company, which engages in the French Southern and Antarctic regions. The company is headquartered in Le Port, Reunion and currently employs 1,029 full-time employees. The firm provides various kinds of fish, including striped trumpeter, skate, southern toothfish, big eye grenadier and yellow fin tuna, as well as St. Paul crayfish and others. The company fishes in the waters of French southern and Antarctic territories, as well as Indian Ocean. Sapmer SA operates through its subsidiaries: Les Armements Reunionnais SAS, specialized in fishing; Armement Sapmer Distribution SARL, engaged in the distribution activities; Armas Peche SAS, which operates the Mascareignes II vessel, engaged in toothfish catch, and 35% of the Austral vessel, engaged in lobster catch, Soparma SAS, an investment entity, and Mer des Mascareignes Ltd, engaged in the processing and conditioning of seafood. As of December 31, 2011, SAPMER INVESTISSEMENTS held an 80% stake in the Company’s shareholdings.

Global Bioenergies SA develops industrial processes to convert renewable sources into isobutene. The company is headquartered in Evry, Ile-De-France and currently employs 55 full-time employees. Isobutene, a hydrocarbon, can be converted into fuels such as isooctane, as well as into various materials (synthetic rubber, organic glass, plastics). The process developed by Global Bioenergies SA is based on the design of an artificial metabolic pathway comprising several enzymes catalyzing reactions not observed in nature. Six patent applications have been filed by the Company. The first two applications covering the key steps of the bio-production of isobutene and other olefins have already been published. The company distributes butane and propane containing bio-isobutene, in a e partnership with Global Bioenergies. The company operates through Syngip.

Théraclion SA develops, manufactures, and markets oncological medical equipment. The company is headquartered in Malakoff, Ile-De-France and currently employs 25 full-time employees. The firm is a a spin-off of Inserm and EDAPTechomed. The main activity of the Company is developping, manufacturing and marketing echotherapy medical equipments associating therapy by focused ultrasound and monitoring by ultrasound. The firm provides Echopulse, a device for the non-invasive and outpatient treatment of the fibroadenoma of the breast and thyroid nodules.

Safwood SpA is an Italy-based company that specializes in processing and trading of timber and its by-products. The Company offers a range of products, such as sawn products, panels, match boards, rebated products, lamellar beams and panels. It is present in a number of markets, notably Italy, Poland, Russia and Ireland, among others. Safwood SpA operates through its subsidiaries, including Leskom and LDK, engaged in forest felling and initial transformation of raw material; Leskom Avto, specialized in the transportation of timber from forest to the works with its own means of transport; Leskom Invest, an investment company; Leskom DSP, which produces chipboard panels; EFI Ltd, involved in the trading activities, and MD, which produces laminated panels, laminated beams, joint strip panels and construction of prefabricated wooden houses.

Amoéba SA engages in developing, manufacturing and biological products. The company is headquartered in Chassieu, Auvergne-Rhone-Alpes and currently employs 23 full-time employees. The firm specializes in disruptive biological solutions for the treatment of Legionella, amoeba and biofilm in water. The firm's offering includes products and services, such as: Cleantech biological solution, a patented technological disruptive product with no impact on the environment; amoebic analyses of waters of wet cooling towers (TAR), hot sanitary waters, industrial waters and waters of swimming pools; as well as Legionella tests of industrial waste water, among others. The firm is engaged in various technical, commercial, industrial and investment partnerships.

ABO-Group Environment NV engages in the management of consulting, engineering, and testing companies. The company is headquartered in Ghent, Oost-Vlaanderen and currently employs 14 full-time employees. The firm operates within following segments: Development, Financing, Fuels, Operations and EPM (Energy Portfolio Management). Development provides project analysis and concept engineering. Financing division finances and co-finances partner projects. Fuels division replaces conventional fuels by alternative and renewable energy sources. Operations sector assumes overall operational and maintenance responsibilities during the lifetime of projects. ABO Group manages operational energy production units in Belgium, the Netherlands and Germany.

Predilife SA is a France-based company specialized in the development of predictive tests in the medical industry. The Company operates mainly in the field of oncology. Predilife offers MammoRisk, which is a predictive breast cancer test that combines medical imaging thanks to a proprietary software, DenSeeMammo, Big Data and statistics through a scoring tool and genetic profiles via a polygenic risk score (PRS). The image is analysed in order to extract the breast density and the first breast cancer risk factor. In addition, The technology used by MammoRisk makes it possible to evaluate from a database of individuals tracked over time, the risks of an individual to develop cancer compared to the fate of his/her closest neighbors through a database of a number of American and French women.

COIL engages in the manufacturing of aluminum. The company is headquartered in Landen, Vlaams-Brabant and currently employs 132 full-time employees. Anodizing is an electrochemical process that transforms the surface of the aluminum into a homogeneous regular film that protects the metal, reinforces its functional qualities, and gives it improved corrosion resistance. Anodized aluminum is used in the construction, transportation, automotive, electronics, architecture, decoration, technology and other markets. The firm operates four production plants in Belgium, Germany and the United Kingdom, it has several production lines, such as continuous coil lines and batch anodizing lines.

Travel Technology Interactive SA engages in software development for air transportation management. The company is headquartered in Paris, Ile-De-France and currently employs 70 full-time employees. The company is a solution provider for the transportation industry specialized in IT software for the management of scheduled airlines, cargo airlines and ferries. TTI's activity comprises software and services, such as operation of call centers, fare management assistance and marketing services, among others. The firm has been an AMADEUS IT GROUP worldwide business partner since 2005 and an IATA Simplifying the Business (StB) Preferred Partner for E-ticketing since August 2006. Its solutions include: Aeropack NG, a complete solution, made up of integrated modules designed for the operational needs of a low cost carrier and FerryPack, including such modules as Inventory Management and Integrated Booking Engine, among others. The company operates globally. As of May 24, 2012, it has opened a new subsidiary Travel Technology Interactive France SAS.

MyBest Group SpA is an Italy-based company engaged in the utility and the e-commerce industry. The Group provides advisory, marketing and research services through a network of specialized consultants and operators. Its service portfolio covers a range of areas, including telecommunication and energy, among others.

Vergnet SA engages in designing, production, marketing and installation of wind energy production plants and potable water supply infrastructures. The company is headquartered in Ormes, Centre and currently employs 111 full-time employees. The company provides wind turbines, water pumps and combined solutions, among others. The company also offers such services as methodological assistance, preliminary analysis of the wind resource and preliminary wind farm calculation, as well as assistance in obtaining project financing. The company also supplies water for rural areas through Vergnet Hydro SAS and is engaged in the field of photovoltaic solar energy through Photalia SAS. Vergnet SA’s customers are electric power companies and independent power producers. The firm is present in France, as well as in the Caribbean, the Pacific, the Indian Ocean, and Africa. It's subsidiaries include Vergnet Pacific SARL, Vergnet Wind Energy Ltd and Energie 21, among others.

Visiomed Group SA is a France-based company engaged in the design, manufacture and marketing of medical electronics. It develops and markets health products in the fields of medical and well-being self-diagnosis to provide non-drug prevention and treatment solutions. The Company's product portfolio comprises MyThermo, an infrared contact-less medical thermometer; MyTension, an automatic blood pressure and pulse monitors; MyOxy, a finger pulse oximeter; MyECG, a pocket electrodiogram; MyGluco, a blood sugar meter; My Coach, a health and fitness coach, and Epiderm, a telemedicine dermatology mobile application, among others. The Company sells its products to pharmacies, health professionals (hospitals, clinics and retirement homes) and to retail chains. Its brand names include ThermoFlash and BewellConnect, among others.

Pharmasimple SA offers online sales of para-pharmaceutical products. The company is headquartered in La Louviere, Hainaut. The firm operates the Website, through which sells pharmaceutical and cosmetics products. Its products portfolio encompasses drugs, food supplements, hygiene, face, body, hair, baby, man, solar, dietetic products, face accessories, anti-aging cream, cleansing cotton, eye contour, eye make-up remover, foaming gel, scrub, cleansing oil, cleansing milk, cleansing wipes, micellar lotion, makeup, mask, foam, oily skin, mixed skin, dry skins, serum, lip sticks, anti-stain care, anti-redness treatment , matifying care, young skin care tonic, and waxing bath sponges and brushes, among others.

Avalon Advanced Materials, Inc. is a mineral exploration and development company, engages in the acquisition, exploration, evaluation, and development of specialty metal and mineral properties. The company is headquartered in Toronto, Ontario. The list of metals and minerals includes lithium, tantalum, niobium, cesium, indium, gallium, germanium, rare earth elements (REE), yttrium, zirconium as well as tin. The firm is in the process of exploring or developing three of its five mineral resource projects, all 100%-owned. The company is currently focusing on its Separation Rapids Lithium Project near Kenora, Ontario and its East Kemptville Tin-Indium Project in Yarmouth, Nova Scotia. The firm operates principally in Canada.

The Blockchain Group SA engages in the provision of data marketing technologies and services. The company is headquartered in Boulogne-Billancourt, Ile-De-France and currently employs 34 full-time employees. The firm provides personalized consumer engagement and retention for advertisers through data publishing, data collection and data enrichment. The firm operates through technology tools for consumer targeting, data-mining and customer relationship management (CRM) according to behavior and context, as well as through platforms for distribution and delivery of customer interactions. Blockchain Group SA develops know-how in performance marketing, generating contacts and customer retention solutions. The firm serves in a number of areas, including the media, travel, health, private sales, finance, and insurance sectors and a platform which provides real-time advertisements, among others.

DLSI engages in the provision of temporary work services. The company is headquartered in Forbach, Grand Est and currently employs 166 full-time employees. The firm has a network of agencies located throughout Europe, including France, Luxembourg, Germany, Poland and Switzerland. DLSI provides temporary employees for its clients in a wide variety of sectors, including insurance, banking, finance and real estate. The firm operates through Assisteo, DLSI Luxembourg SA, DLSI GMBH, PEMSA SA, PEMSA VAUD SA, PEMSA GE SA, Select Emploi, Marine Interim, DLSI Polska, Tercio, IM-V, Society-V CH, Bova Service SA, Emo France, MT Interim and Tiro Personal AG, among others.

Stradim-Espace Finances SA engages in real estate and property development. The company is headquartered in Entzheim, Grand Est and currently employs 109 full-time employees. The firm is active domestically, mainly in Alsace, Champagne-Ardennes, Midi-Pyrenees and Pays de la Loire regions. The firm operates through its subsidiaries, including Espace Promotion SAS, Espace Foncier SARL, Habitat Services SARL, Espace Participations SARL and MC Bat SARL, among others.

Theradiag SA engages in the distribution, development and manufacturing of in vitro diagnostic and theranostics tests. The company is headquartered in Croissy-Beaubourg, Ile-De-France and currently employs 61 full-time employees. The firm develops and offers product panels for diagnosing autoimmune diseases, allergies, and infectious diseases. TheraDiags product offering consists of tests using a range of techniques (Elisa, rapid tests, immunofluorescence, Dot, immunochemical tests, molecular biology, etc.) as well as a range of automatic devices and solutions for high-speed diagnostics based on Luminexs Multiplex technology. The company has also developed a range of theranostic diagnostics commercialized under the Lisa-Tracker brand which provide monitoring of patients treated by anti-TNF monoclonal antibodies. TheraDiag is active in more than 30 countries, as an independent distributor.

HiTechPros SA provides outsourcing services in the Information Technology sector. The company is headquartered in Montrouge, Ile-De-France and currently employs 16 full-time employees. The firm operates a Website, www.hitechpros.com, which serves as a Web-based marketplace, intended for putting entities in the IT market in touch with each other, as well as providing assistance for chief information officers, by connecting them with the IT resources. Hitechpros SA’s clients include IT services companies, freelance consultants and training specialists, among others. As of December 31, 2011, the Company operates through its wholly owned subsidiary Hitechliberty SARL.

Ada SA engages in the transportation business. The company is headquartered in Clichy, Ile-De-France and currently employs 112 full-time employees. Its offer includes commercial and non-commercial vehicles, including cabriolets, minibuses, city cars and two wheels vehicles to both individuals and businesses. Ada SA also offers removal vehicles to private individuals. As of December 31, 2011, the Company develops a network of franchises that operate a number of over 400 agencies located throughout France, Guadeloupe, Guyana, Mauritius, Martinique, New Caledonia, La Reunion and Dominican Republic. The company is also operational through several subsidiaries, including Sapn, Holiday Bikes, Adabox, Ada Courtage, EDA, Issy Location, Beziers Locations, Keyvanne, Neuilly Location and Limoges Location. Ada SA is a part of G7 Entreprises. In May 17, 2013, it decided to merge with two of its wholly-owned subsidiaries, SAPN and Issy Location, in order to simplify its legal structure.

Intrasense SA engages in the design and development of advanced software solutions for viewing and analyzing of medical images. The company is headquartered in Montpellier, Occitanie and currently employs 31 full-time employees. The Company’s activities are divided into three divisions: sales of software for viewing and analyzing medical images; development of peripheral solutions;and supply of services. Its product portfolio comprises the Myrian line products are integrated into existing medical devices, such as Cr, Ultra sound and Nuclear imagining. Myrian Solutions are used for reconstruction of images from the Computed tomography(CT) scan, Magnetic Resonance Imaging (MRI) and Positron Emission Tomography scans, marketed under Myrian brand. The peripheral solutions provide materials for viewing digital images in the operating room, as well as various equipment, including printing servers and workstations, among others. The company offers also support, maintenance, as well as software rental and installation services for its products.

MG International designs and manufactures immersion detectors for swimming pools. The company is headquartered in La Ciotat, Paca and currently employs 250 full-time employees. The firm produces and sells a range of equipment for private and public swimming pools, such as Aquasensor and Aqualarm alarms that sound when people fall into swimming pools; Poseidon, computer assisted surveillance systems for the prevention against drownings and Aqualife, automatic coverings for swimming pools. MG International sells its products directly to swimming pool builders and distributors. MG International SA operates essentially in France, in Europe and in the United States through its subsidiaries including, MG Brazil, MG Iberica, Poseidon Technologies Inc and Safeblue. The firm is controlled by Maytronics Ltd.

UPERGY SA distributes consumable products for professionals and individuals. The company is headquartered in Champagne-Au-Mont-D Or, Auvergne-Rhone-Alpes and currently employs 303 full-time employees. The company operates through two divisions: Battery Division and Health & Safety Division. The Battery Division offers portable energy solutions, such as batteries, chargers and accumulators. The Health & Safety Division, operated by the Company's PRORISK business, specializes in the distribution of health and safety products, protective clothing and first aid equipment. Its main sectors of activity are the food industry, pharmaceuticals, cosmetics, medical and paramedical. Products are distributed via a network of stores and franchise stores, mail order, call centers, printed and electronic catalogues, and dedicated websites. The firm operates through a number of subsidiaries, including All Batteries UK Limited, VDI Espana, and Power trade France, among others.

Avcorp Industries, Inc. engages in the design and manufacture of airframe structures and aircraft assembly products. The company is headquartered in Delta, British Columbia and currently employs 369 full-time employees. The firm offers integrated composite and metallic aircraft structures to aircraft manufacturers. The company is a supplier for engineering design, manufacture and assembly of subassemblies and complete structures for aircraft manufacturers. The company operates from over two locations in Canada and a location in the United States. Comtek Advanced Structures Ltd. (Comtek), its subsidiary located in Ontario, offers aircraft structural component repair services for commercial aircraft. Within Comtek Advanced Structures Ltd., exists two divisions: Comtek and Avcorp Engineered Composites, which are engaged in design and manufacture of small-sized composite aerostructures. Located in Gardena, California, Avcorp Composite Fabrication Inc. (ACF) is engaged in medium and large composite aerostructures fabrication.

Allbanc Split Corp. II is a Canada-based mutual fund company. The Company's principal activity is to invest in common shares (Portfolio Shares) of Bank of Montreal, Canadian Imperial Bank of Commerce, National Bank of Canada, Royal Bank of Canada, The Bank of Nova Scotia and The Toronto-Dominion Bank. The Company holds a portfolio of common shares of Bank of Montreal, Canadian Imperial Bank of Commerce, National Bank of Canada, The Bank of Nova Scotia, Royal Bank of Canada and The Toronto-Dominion Bank (the Portfolio Shares) in order to generate income for the holders of its preferred shares (the Preferred Shares) and to enable the holders of its Capital Shares to participate in any capital appreciation in the Portfolio Shares and to benefit from any increase in the dividends payable on the Portfolio Shares. It invests in Portfolio Shares and does not engage in trading except in limited circumstances, including fund retractions or redemptions of Capital Shares and Preferred Shares.

Global EcoPower SA engages in the construction and development of green and alternative energy project. The company is headquartered in Meyreuil, Paca and currently employs 9 full-time employees. The firm covers all development stages to electricity production, including land prospecting, drafting and signature of leases, technical studies, modeling, technical and financial optimization, impact studies, administrative requirements, search for suppliers, organization, piloting and coordination, reception, industrial commissioning, financing and client prospection. The firm operates through subsidiaries, including Solar EcoPower, BTP Consult, Global Ecopower Construction, AT Farming and AT Solaire. The company operates through Mse Le Haut Des Epinettes SAS.

UV Germi SA designs and manufactures UV reactors which are used in the applications of drinking & waste water, water in public swimming pools, rain water, air, surfaces, and industrial water. The company is headquartered in St-Viance, Nouvelle-Aquitaine and currently employs 41 full-time employees. The company develops and manufactures a range of UV sterilizers for water treatment. Its sterilizers consist of low pressure mercury vapor lamps, which emit a monochromatic wavelength aimed at destruction of microorganisms. The lamps placed either in cylindrical tubes or canalization, with thin layers of water circulating around them and water components absorbing UV radiation. The applications of the Company's technology include dechloramination of swimming pools, treatment of drinking, rain and waste water, fountains and ponds disinfection, industrial water treatment, aquarium cleaning, and air treatment, purification and disinfection, among others.

U10 Corp. SA engages in the design, creation, and distribution of product lines for home decoration. The company is headquartered in Lyon, Auvergne-Rhone-Alpes and currently employs 376 full-time employees. The firm has three product ranges: home textile, home utility and leisure goods and personal leisure goods and accessories. They include soft furnishings and decor, tableware, bed and bath linen, household goods, leisure items, fragrance and cosmetics, special occasion items like Christmas and party decorations, footwear, under garments and luggage. As of December 31, 2011, U10 operates through several subsidiaries, including L3C, a France-based company engaged in the production of textiles for home decoration; Smerwick Group, a China-based company engaged in tablecloths manufacturing, and ID World, a France-based company which designs leisure goods. In October 2013, it announced that Financiere des Docks SAS has raised its stake in U10 SA to 57.453% by acquiring additional 19.173% from the share capital.

Wedia SA provides publishing content management software and cross-media publishing dedicated for the press, media, and business sector. The company is headquartered in Paris, Ile-De-France and currently employs 60 full-time employees. helps global companies engage in more profitable dialogues with local or segmented customers and prospects by empowering individuals at the point of impact, making globally distributed marketers, salespeople, stores and branches more agile by moving the design, production, editing and distribution of valuable marketing assets to the point of impact while also ensure message consistency across three channels. Print pedigree, helps newspapers print editorial system to publish daily editions; Web expertise, which helps to create, preview, validate, and publish content to multiple websites, in different languages and in various formats and Mobile innovation, integrated mobile capability. Wedia SA’s clients include Accor, Dior, Societe Generale and SFR, among others. The company operates through Damdy.

Nextedia SA engages in the provision of internet marketing services. The company is headquartered in Paris, Ile-De-France and currently employs 141 full-time employees. The Group provides its customers with business and technological expertise, coupled with end-to-end support from consulting to the implementation of market solutions. The firm reports its businesses into four main segments: Omnicanal Customer Relationship Management (CRM), which includes customer relationship management, contact center and multichannel interactions; Digital Marketing, which encompasses CRM Marketing & Data Driven; Digital Experience, which includes Web & mobile factory, design thinking, UX design and user experience; Smart Data, which includes Big Data preparation, information architecture (IA) and Data science. Its services cover a number of sectors, including banking and insurance, health, mutual and personal protection, media and telecom and industry and energy, among others.

M2i SA engages in the provision of professional training services. The company is headquartered in Paris, Ile-De-France and currently employs 169 full-time employees. The firm has training centers in such French cities as Aix en Provence, Angouleme, Bordeaux, la Rochelle, Lille, Nantes, Poitiers, Rennes, Saint-Etienne, Sophia Antipolis and Strasbourg. The firm provides its services under the brand names Scribtel, Avolys and M2i Formation. Maison Internationale de l'Informatique SA is a subsidiary of Groupe O2i. The firm operates through its wholly owned subsidiaries, Scriptel Formation and Formatic. In addition, the Company manages approximately 33 training centers.

Bluelinea SA engages in the design and development of electronic surveillance and medical tele-assistance systems. The company is headquartered in Elancourt, Ile-De-France and currently employs 72 full-time employees. Bluelinea SA specializes in designing and developing electronic surveillance and medical teleassistance systems. The company offers caregiver identification and authentication badges, individual protection bracelets for newborns, and home care and treatment devices for fragile or chronically ill elderly persons. The firm cooperates with Europe-based partners, including Everon Oy/Ab and Hager group, among others.

Invibes Advertising SA provides digital in-feed advertising services. The company is headquartered in Gand (Gent), Oost-Vlaanderen. The firm is specialized giving advice, assisting, acting as an intermediary in the design, implementation, execution and management of orders and projects in online advertising, where it offers more than 30 advertising services, including interactive video views, in-feed format, among others. The company controls the entire broadcast chain, including ad serving and targeting, formats and direct publisher relationship, among others. The firm provides its services to media groups, such as Teamedia, CCMBenchmark or Lagardere, among others. Furthermore, around 200 brands has adopted Invibes in-feed format advertisement, including McDonald, IBM, Volkswagen or Airfrance, among others.

Montagne & Neige Développement SA engages in the development, equipping and protection of ski resorts, leisure facilities, access roads and other mountain infrastructure. The company is headquartered in Sainte-Helene-Du-Lac, Auvergne-Rhone-Alpes and currently employs 371 full-time employees. The company is active in the field of mountain infrastructure and a low-impact and alternative mode of urban transport. The firm operates in three main sectors: Mountain, Cableway Urban Transport and Process. The Mountain sector includes safety, leisure, snowmaking and ski lifts; the Cableway Urban Transport include cable-mounted urban transport system designed to fit into urban and peri-urban environments; Process segment is engaged in the production and warehousing activities of the Company.

Uniti SA is a France-based company specialized in the construction and promotion of assisted housing. The Group mainly specializes in social housing, student homes and senior residences. The Company operates through a number of agencies, which includes Paris agency, Sete agency, Marseille agency, and Valenciennes agency. Uniti SA uses a range of financing solutions, such as classic financing, crowd funding, investment funds and stock exchange. Uniti SA operates in a number of cities in France, including Montpelier, Arras, Bordeaux and Paris, among others.

Europlasma SA is a France-based company that offers a range of solutions for hazardous waste treatment. The Company’s technology allows converting toxic waste into reusable materials. The Company is composed of four entities, such as Europlasma Torch & Process, which provides engineering consulting for hazardous waste treatment, and sells and licenses its plasma torches and technology; Inertam SAS, which specializes in destruction and valorization of asbestos waste and operates ash melting units; CHO Power SAS, which supplies technological solutions for the efficient transformation of biomass and waste into electric energy and Europe Environnement, which offers ventilation and air cleaning systems for industrial applications.

Altur Investissement SAC, formerly Turenne Investissement SCA is a France-based capital investment company. The Company specializes in Owner Buy-Out and Leveraged Buy-Out investments in small and medium-sized French companies. Turenne Investment co-invests with funds managed by Turenne Capital Partenaires. The Company invests mainly in four sectors: healthcare, specialized distribution, services and sustainable development. The Company has stakes in various companies, including Aston Medical and Capsule Technologie, representing the healthcare sector, International Greetings, HPE, Quemco, Somedics and Pellenc Selective Technologies, among others.

genOway SA engages in the development of genetically-modified mouse, rat, and cellular models for biopharmaceutical and research companies. The company is headquartered in Lyon, Auvergne-Rhone-Alpes and currently employs 125 full-time employees. The firm offers a range of services, comprising site specific transgenesis, random insertion based transgenic models, gene overexpression, humanization, gene deletion and gene knock-down (RNA interference). In addition, genOway SA's clients have access to its validated tool and consultancy services from a dedicated project manager. The Company’s clients include multinational biopharmaceutical companies, such as Roche, Novartis and Servier, as well as universities and research institutes, notably Boston University, University of Tokyo, Johann Wolfgang Goethe University Hospital Frankfurt and Centre National de Genotypage. The company has also formed partnerships with Charles River Laboratories, Altana Pharma, Dainihon Sumitomo Pharmceuticals and Euratools, among others.

Poulaillon SA engages in the food industry. The company is headquartered in Wittelsheim, Grand Est and currently employs 829 full-time employees. The firm offers a wide range of services, including buffets (salads, sea products, meats, cold cuts), bakery products with cheese, snacks (sandwiches, pretzels) and pastries (caes, muffins, croissants, fruit, desserts, as well as chocolate fountains), among others. The firm delivers caterings in the Region of Alsace, but it also delivers its products outside the Region for a special order. In addition, Poulaillon SA sells its products in a chain of retail stores throughout France.

Rougier SA is a France-based producer of wood. Through its subsidiaries, Rougier SA sells logs, sawn timber and plywood produced in its forest and industrial units in Central Africa (Gabon and Congo, among others) throughout the world. In addition, the Company provides semi-finished products, such as decking and benches, among others. In France, Rougier has two import sales networks: Rougier Sylvaco, a specialist in various forms of tropical wood and Rougier Panneaux, a specialist in plywood panels. Rougier SA has a number of subsidiaries, including Mokabi, SPS International and Rougier Gabon, among others. The Company trades approximately 70 tropical wood species globally in more than 50 countries.

Plant Advanced Technologies SA operates as a plant biotechnology company. The company is headquartered in Vandouevre-Les-Nancy, Grand Est and currently employs 35 full-time employees. The company is also engaged in the research and development in the field of plant biotechnology. The firm patented its own production technologies, such as PAT Plant Milking, active natural compounds production system based on roots exudation of plants grown hydroponically or PAT Friday, a recombinant protein expression system using natural protein excretion system of genetically modified carnivorous to produce outside their leaf, in a sterile closed pitcher, the protein of interest in liquid. In addition PAT is involved in the development and sale of know-how, licenses and sub-licenses for its technologies.

Cogra 48 SA engages in the production and sale of wood pellets. The company is headquartered in Mende, Occitanie and currently employs 47 full-time employees. The firm is engaged in the manufacturing and sale of wood pellets for use in boilers and stoves, and it also imports Harman stoves from the United States, such as Advance, Accentra, XXV and Accentra Insert, among others, which are sold via a distribution network throughout France. Moreover Cogra 48 SA is engaged in the wholesale of Froling boilers specifically the P4 model, as well as in consulting, project planning, assistance in project management and after-sale support activities. The firm operates two production plants in France, located in Mende and Craponne sur Arzon, as well as a storage unit in Mende for stoves and boilers.

Media-Maker SpA is an Italy-based company focused on the development and production of branded content. It operates through three business line: Content, Media and TV (television) productions. The Content business line produces content and creates cross-media projects for costumers providing editorial offices support, different communication channels and video production support. The Media business line manages different types of communication channels, such as info pad inside shopping malls, rotors next to newsstands, outdoor, paper adv, among others. The TV production business line produces audiovisual content, such as, inter alia, tv programs, advertising and multimedia contents for cinema, television, corporate companies and their brands, and for the Company’s Web-Platform. Such video productions range over different genres, such as, inter alia, entertainment, reality, game shows, lifestyle, documentary, animation, talk shows, drama, comedy and kids shows.

ABIONYX Pharma SA engages in the in discovery and development of novel therapies for patients without existing or effective treatments. The company is headquartered in Balma, Occitanie and currently employs 14 full-time employees. The Company’s product portfolio comprises Cerenis HDL and HDL enhancers that is designed to regress atherosclerotic plaque among patients at high risk of cardiovascular events, among others. Additionally, the Company has a portfolio of clinical and preclinical HDL programs. The firm is present in Labege in Midi-Pyrenees in France and in Ann Arbor in Michigan in the United States. In addition, it also operates through LYPRO Biosciences Inc.

Devernois SA engages in the design, production, and marketing of women's clothing and accessories. The company is headquartered in Le Coteau, Auvergne-Rhone-Alpes and currently employs 307 full-time employees. The firm offers apparel and accessories for women, including suits, blouses, sweaters, skirts, pants, jackets and dresses, among others. As of December 31, 2013, Devernois SA had over 80 branches in France, including eight stands in department stores and 12 affiliated and abroad (Spain, Switzerland, Belgium, Luxembourg and Portugal), 29 branches including over 10 in concession of department stores (Innos, Corte Ingles, Loeb) and three affiliates. As of December 31, 2013 the Company operated through five subsidiaries: Sofrade SA, with its subsidiaries Italie 6 SARL and Devernois Belgique SARL; Devernois Espana SL, Socad SARL, Devernois Luxembourg SARL and Devernois Portugal LDA.

Ashford, Inc. engages in the provision of asset management, advisory services and other products and services primarily to clients in the hospitality industry. The company is headquartered in Dallas, Texas and currently employs 116 full-time employees. The firm operates in the segment of asset and investment management, which includes managing the day-to-day operations of Ashford Hospitality Prime, Inc. (Ashford Prime) and its subsidiaries. The firm serves as the advisor to Ashford Prime, an New York Stock Exchange (NYSE)-listed real estate investment trust (REIT) that invests primarily in high revenue per available room (RevPAR), luxury, upper-upscale and upscale hotels in gateway and resort locations. The firm also serves as the advisor to Ashford Hospitality Trust, Inc. (Ashford Trust), which is focused on investing opportunistically in the hospitality industry with a focus on upscale and upper-upscale hotels in the United States. The firm conducts its business and owns substantially all of its assets through an operating entity, Ashford Hospitality Advisors LLC (Ashford LLC).

AgroGeneration SA operates as an agricultural company, which engages in the production of agricultural commodities. The company is headquartered in Paris, Ile-De-France and currently employs 1,132 full-time employees. The firm is a producer of grain and oilseeds. Following its merger with Harmelia, the Company becomes the producer of grain and oilseeds in Ukraine. Agrogeneration SA focuses mainly on the production in Ukraine, both in terms of cultivated acreage and operational efficiency. The firm follows traditional crop rotation and puts money into fertilizers, seeds, and agricultural chemicals for the purpose of achieving profitability crop. Operated farmlands of Agrogeneration SA are located in a number of regions in Ukraine, such as Kharkiv, Lviv and Sumy, among others, which represent standards and a propitious climate for achieving yields.

Anevia SA develops and supplies telecommunication equipment. The company is headquartered in Gentilly, Ile-De-France and currently employs 80 full-time employees. The firm provides Internet Protocol television (IPTV) over-the-top (OTT) TV solutions for live and on-demand video streaming to television sets, computers, tablets and mobile phones. With over 1,000 deployments in 70 countries, Anevia delivers video solutions to telecommunication operators, broadcast service providers and the hospitality market. Anevia offers a range of carrier grade products that can stream live and on-demand video across managed Internet Protocol (IP) networks or through the Internet. Its solutions cover the entire value chain from live ingestion with digital video broadcasting (DVB) to IP gateways, content distribution management, content conversion, monitoring and load balancing, through to video servers for Video on Demand (VOD) and catch-up TV. The company also provides product training and consulting and installation services.

Alès Groupe SA designs, manufactures, and markets plant-based cosmetic and capillary products. The company is headquartered in Paris, Ile-De-France and currently employs 1,081 full-time employees. The firm produces dermo-cosmetic treatments, as well as hair treatments designed for individuals and hairdressing professionals. The company also produces hair-coloring products under the brand name Ducastel. The firm sells its products also under another brands, such as Phyto,Secret Professionnel, PhytoSpecific, and Kydra. Skincare products are sold under the brand name Lierac and perfumes are sold under the brand name Caron. The firm operates various subsidiaries located in France, the United Kingdom, Canada, Benelux, Poland and other countries, such as Boy Diffusion, Parfums Caron, PhytoSolba, Caster, Phytales, Ales Groupe Industrie and Ales Groupe Inc, among others. As of December 31, 2011, S.A.S. Avila held an 80.57% stake in the Company’s shareholdings.

NSC Groupe SA engages in the design and manufacture of equipment for the textile and packaging industries. The company is headquartered in Guebwiller, Grand Est and currently employs 226 full-time employees. The company operates through four business divisions: Textiles division, which manufactures industrial machinery that produces yarns from natural and synthetic fibers and is engaged in developing integrated production lines for the production of textile fabrics in a continuous process; the Packaging division, which designs and manufactures winders and uncoilers for paper packaging industry; the Foundry division, which is equipped in automatic casting shops specially designed for the production of parts in lamellar graphite iron or ductile cast iron and Environment division, which designs and markets hydroelectric micro-power plants operated by means of hydrodynamic screws under the trade name Ell3o. The firm also supplies control systems and supervisory systems to monitor industrial production lines and it offers a range of services.

NOXXON Pharma NV is a clinical-stage biopharmaceutical company, which focuses on cancer treatment. The company is headquartered in Berlin, Berlin and currently employs 11 full-time employees. The firm's main product is the Spiegelmer platform. Spiegelmers are a variant of a drug class called aptamers, which are based on deoxyribonucleic acid (DNA) or ribonucleic acid (RNA) and are built on a backbone of mirror-image RNA or DNA - L-stereoisomers. The firm's lead candidate, NOX-A12, is under development as a combination therapy for a number of cancer indications using immuno-oncology approaches, such as immune checkpoint inhibition and current standards of care, such as chemotherapy and radiotherapy. The firm also develops NOX-E36, which is aimed at the treatment of complications arising from diabetic nephropathy.

UCAR is a holding company, which engages in the provision of car rental services. The company is headquartered in Boulogne-Billancourt, Ile-De-France and currently employs 74 full-time employees. The firm offers its customers the choice to rent passenger cars and utility vehicles from half a day to up to three days and also offers leasing contracts for up to three years. Its points of sales are divided into franchises, as well as affiliates. Ucar SA has several subsidiaries: Ucar Location, which manages the franchises of the Company; Ucar Developpement, which is in charge of the management of affiliates; Ucar Fleet, which acts as the purchasing division of the Company; SS2A Courtage, which is in charge of insurance brokerage activities; and Societe Nouvelle de l’Estey, which focuses on key business accounts and the white label network.
