Filae SA operates an internet portal that specializes in family and identity tracking. The company is headquartered in Paris, Ile-De-France and currently employs 50 full-time employees. The firm's main Website, www.notrefamille.com, provides information and services for families and parents. Its features include forums for parents to interact with other parents; a facility to create a family Website by uploading photographs and other details, and articles on health, lifestyle, recipes and parenting tips. Beside www.Notrefamille.com, the Company owns other Websites such as www.Cadeaux.com, www.Genealogie.com, www.Familles.com, www.Prenoms.com, www.Citations.com and www.Mediadico.com. The Websites provide online information on offering gifts, information to enable clients to research their ancestors and family history, such as census records, historical documents and information on the origins of surnames and popular first names for children, among other information.

Trilogiq SA manufactures tubular systems. The company is headquartered in Saint Ouen L Aumone, Ile-De-France and currently employs 297 full-time employees. The Company’s products and services are used to reduce non-productive areas, decrease operator movements, and optimize ergonomics, costs, and production times. Its activities are divided in four main business lines: modular supports, which are products consisting of small packaging boxes with various functions, carts, assembly work stations and multi-department supermarkets. The firm distributes its products under the brand name LeanTek. Trilogiq SA has a number of subsidiaries in various countries, such as Germany, the United States, Australia, Brazil, Poland, Hungary, Slovakia and Belgium, among others.

Advenis SA engages in the provision of asset and fund management services. The company is headquartered in Paris, Ile-De-France and currently employs 300 full-time employees. The Group serves a number of sectors, including institutional and private clients. Advenis SA divides its services into three core businesses: Asset Production and Management, which includes a range of real estate solutions that enable to seize market opportunities while remaining adapted to investors' profiles, financial assets and a range of real estate funds ( SCPI); Wealth Management and Distribution, which encompasses various real estate and financial products, services delivered to institutional and private clients, wealth management, institutional sales, key accounts and services provided by independent financial advisers ( IFA), and Real Estate Services, which includes asset management, property management, facility management, brokerage and advisory.

Moulinvest SA produces and sells wood products. The company is headquartered in Dunieres, Auvergne-Rhone-Alpes and currently employs 193 full-time employees. The firm provides wood cutting services and manufactures finished wood products aimed at the building industry, such as beams and timber frame structures for houses. The firm also uses the waste from its primary activity using biomass to produce electricity and heat, as well as manufacturing wood pellets to be used in heating systems. Moulinvest SA sources its wood from forests in the Auvergne and Rhone-Alpes regions of France. The firm has various direct subsidiaries, such as Scierie Moulin, which regroups the wood cutting activities of the Company, and Moulin Bois Energie, which focuses on the renewable energy activities of the Company. Moulinvest SA also has an indirect subsidiary, SCI de Ville, a real estate company which owns the building used by Scierie Moulin.

Miliboo SA engages in manufacturing and marketing of furniture and decorative objects. The company is headquartered in Chavanod, Auvergne-Rhone-Alpes. is a France-based company engaged in the design, manufacture and sale of home furnishings. The firm manages an online store available in various European countries. The firm sells products such as sofas, armchairs, desks, chairs, bar stools, tables (including coffee tables, dining tables and others), storage furniture (including shelves and sideboards, among others), garden furnishings, decorative elements and bathroom furniture, as well as carpets, lamps, decorative fireplaces, mirrors, pictures, folding screens, among others. MILIBOO.COM S.A.S. provides its products across the French market.

KERLINK SA provides end-to-end network solutions for the Internet of Things, serving telecom operators, businesses and public authorities. The company is headquartered in Thorigne-Fouillard, Bretagne and currently employs 125 full-time employees. Its solutions enable communication between companies’ information systems and fixed equipment, such as electricitys meters, and vehicles, including public transport and railway wagons. The firm's various solutions are divided into three main segments: Public operators, which includes a range of products, such as Wirnet Station 868 MHz, Wirnet Station 915 MHz, Wirnet Station 920/925 MHz and Wirnet Station SPN; Private operators, which includes LoRa IoT Station Range, Wirgrid Range, Wirma Range and Wirtrack Range, and End-Points that includes Wirma Gateway 2, Wirma Gateway 2 R, Wirgrid Station and Wirgrid Collect 868.

Arcure SA is a France-based company specialized in the technology sector. The Company develops a range of solutions for enhancing the autonomy of industrial machinery. Arcure SA serves companies operating within construction, transport, tunnels or urban cleanup, logistics and the mining sector. Its portfolio includes two main products: Blaxtair and Omega. Blaxtair offers solutions for securing the perimeter around mobile industrial machinery and robots by preventing collision in working environments. Omega is an advanced stereoscopic camera calculating the disparity map by providing metadata to the user. Additionally, thanks to its two sensors, Omega provides the disparity map and raw images at 20 frames per seconds. Apart from France, the Company also operates in a number of countries, which includes Japan, Chile and England, among others.

IntegraGen SA engages in the development of genetic biomarkers. The company is headquartered in Evry, Ile-De-France and currently employs 42 full-time employees. The company researches and develops biomarkers for use as diagnostic tools in the fields of autism, oncology, diabetes and obesity. The company uses an evaluation model with several autism-related genes using a combination of several common polymorphisms (Single-Nucleotide Polymorphism or SNP or common variant). The company also develops molecular biomarker validation programs for Hepatocellular Carcinoma and anti-epidermal growth factor receptor (anti-EGFR) resistance markers. The firm also provides genomics services to practitioners and researchers, such as DNA extraction, marker selection and tagging and bioinformatical analysis of sequence data in such fields as pharmacogenetics, cytogenetics, epigenetics, search for mutations and SNP discovery, among others. As of December 31, 2011, the Company operated through a wholly owned subsidiary, IntegraGen Inc.

Mecelec Composites SA engages in the manufacture of composite materials. The company is headquartered in Mauves, Auvergne-Rhone-Alpes and currently employs 250 full-time employees. The company offers a range of multi-energy connection equipment, metering equipment, protection and cut-out boxes, as well as shut-off, pressure regulation and metering boxes and others. In addition, the Company provides a range of distribution boxes. The firm is active in two main markets: Networks with a range of junction boxes to networks of electricity, gas, water and telecom and the industry by providing solutions for a range of industrial applications. The company has sites located in France, as well as in Romania. The company operates through, including Mecelec Plastic Compozit (Roumanie), Mecelec Industries (France).

Neolife SAS manufactures and distributes enviromental friendly construction materials. The company is headquartered in Limonest, Auvergne-Rhone-Alpes. The firm divides its offer in six product lines. The Outlife line provides exterior design solutions, such as cladding, insulated facade systems, outdoor joinery and covering systems. The Inlife division supplies interior design components, including partitions, linings and movable walls. The Sunlife’s offering includes terrace decking and systems, privacy screens, fencing and water walls. The Streetlife division manufactures street furniture, walkway sand and landscaping features. The Homelife line is engaged in the area of living spaces, and provides complete building solutions, garages, carports and summer houses. The Techlife line produces bio-sourced and recycled materials. The Company’s main product is VESTA, Vegetal, Ecological Stable Timber Advantage, an environmental material based on wood fibers.

Groupe Tera SA is a France-based company active in the measurement, analysis and real-time valuation of air quality. The Group is present on the entire air quality value chain, thus meeting all the needs of its customers by relying on three complementary and synergistic activities: a laboratory specialized in the analysis of chemical air pollutants for all environments, an activity of design, development and commercialization of sensors for the real-time measurement of the quality of air and a digital offer, consisting of an innovative professional analysis software capable of processing the air quality data collected by the sensors.

Lucibel SA engages in the design, manufacture, and marketing of lighting products and solutions from LED technology. The company is headquartered in Reuil-Malmaison, Ile-De-France and currently employs 133 full-time employees. The firm produces bulbs in a number of different categories, including relamping, ambiance lighting, architectural lighting, accentuation lighting, bulbs for warehouses and industry and outdoor lighting. The firm also produces related equipment such as drivers, rings and suspension cables. Lucibel SA's products can be bought online or via its network of distributors and resellers. The firm also provides technical and commercial services, including studies into which kind of lighting is suited to a particular project, as well as installation and monitoring.

O2i SA engages in the provision of computer hardware and software integration services for professionals in the digital graphics industry. The company is headquartered in Gennevilliers, Ile-De-France and currently employs 229 full-time employees. The Company’s activities include vocational training, digital printing, services, distribution, telecommunication solutions, management of production flow and audio-video solutions. The company also provides hardware installation and maintenance services, software installation, information management services and training, The Company’s portfolio of clients includes photoengravers, printers, publishers and communication groups, such as L'Oreal, Lafarge, Sonia Rykiel, Credit Suisse, EDF, among others. In September 2013, it announced the acquisition of information technology training business Bull Formation (Bull Training). In February 2014, it acquired the commercial fund Kolorsigns.

IVALIS SA develops inventory management solutions to the retail sector. The company is headquartered in Montigny Le Bretonneux, Ile-De-France and currently employs 391 full-time employees. The firm offers various types of services: turnkey inventories, which provide companies with all the means for executing an inventory, such as information technology hardware and software, and qualified personnel, and partner inventories, whereby L'Inventoriste SA’s personnel and resources work in cooperation with the client's resources. The firm operates eight subsidiaries: Ivalis France and Ivalis Technology, based in France; Ivalis Inventarios, based in Spain; Ivalis Belgium form Belgium; Ivalis Italia based in Italy, Ivalis ; Ivalis Nederland and Ivalis Deutschland. L'Inventoriste SA has 15 French offices, as well as agencies in Spain, Portugal, Italy, Poland, Germany, the Netherlands and in Belgium. In June 2013, it announced the acquisition of the German group Sigma, a provider of inventory outsourcing in Germany and Switzerland.

Deinove SA is a biotechnology company, which engages in the development of new-generation anti-infective antibiotics and bioactives. The company is headquartered in Grabels, Occitanie and currently employs 60 full-time employees. The company specializes in the development and commercial exploitation of processes for production of biofuels and other compounds of industrial or pharmaceutical value. The processes developed by Deinove use the natural properties of Deinococcus bacteria. The green chemistry process includes the production of organic acids, such as succinic, lactic, fumaric and butyric acids used in the petrochemical, pharmaceutical, cosmetics and food industries. In addition, the Company is engaged in the production of antibiotics and antifungal agents. Deinove SA operates with such industrial companies as Tereos, CNRS, VTT, BENP-Lillebonne and Nosopharm, among others. The firm's main shareholder is Fonds Truffle Capital. The company operates through DEINOBIOTICS and Deinobiotics SAS, among others.

KKO International SA engages in the production and export of cocoa beans. The company is headquartered in Bruxelles, Bruxelles-Capitale. The firm specializes in the cultivation of cocoa trees, as well as farming and harvesting of cocoa beans in Ivory Coast. The company also owns a banana and teak plantation. The firm operates through a number of subsidiaries, such as Solea.

Akita Drilling Ltd. engages in the drilling solutions in the field of oil and natural gas. The company is headquartered in Calgary, Alberta and currently employs 1,085 full-time employees. The firm is involved in other forms of drilling, including potash mining and the development of storage caverns. The firm owns and operates approximately 31 drilling rigs in Canada. The firm manages its business through approximately two geographic regions, which include Canada and the United States. The firm specializes in the construction and retrofit of heavy oil pad drilling rigs associated with Steam Assisted Gravity Drainage (SAGD) operations. Its rigs are used in operations spanning Fort McMurray, the Alberta oil sands region. The firm also has shale gas operations in the Horn River Basin area of Northeast British Columbia. AKITA is involved in drilling horizontal shale gas wells, with a fleet of deep capacity triple rigs in the areas of Alberta and British Columbia, including the Montney, Duvernay and Horn River regions.

Osmozis SA provides wireless connection services. The company is headquartered in Clapiers, Occitanie and currently employs 60 full-time employees. The firm focuses on the supply and operation of wireless (Wi-Fi) multi-service networks in European holiday centers. The firm's services range comprises Flexible Wi-Fi, a mobile Wi-Fi access and hotspots; OsmoConnect, a certification for third-parties connected to Osmozis network; OsmoCam, a closed-circuit television (CCTV); Canal-Info, an informative television canal; OsmoAlert, a mobile alert in case of hotel emergency, and OsmoCheck, a network management software. The firm also invents, develops, manufactures, tests, installs and operates its Wi-Fi networks and associated connected devices solutions. Osmozis SAS operates through Logmis.

Alpha MOS SA engages in the manufacture, development, and marketing of sensory analysis equipment. The company is headquartered in Toulouse, Occitanie and currently employs 77 full-time employees. The firm develops sensing technologies that digitize the human senses and can provide an odor (electronic noses), taste (electronic tongues) or chemical profile (gas chromatography instruments) of a product. Alpha Mos SA provides instruments for chemical and organoleptic analysis, lab outsourcing services in sensory or chemical analysis, technical and application support and development of industrial customized solutions. Its products are used in the food, cosmetics and packaging fields, as well as in the petrochemical, pharmaceutical and medical sectors. The firm operates through subsidiaries: Alpha MOS America Inc, Alpha Mos Japan KK, Alpha MOS UK Ltd, Alpha MOS (Shanghai) Instruments Trading Co WOFE and BOYD Sense Inc in San Francisco. The main shareholder of the Company are Jolt Capital and Ambrosia Investments.

Alliance Développement Capital SIIC engages in the acquisition and construction of buildings for lease. The company is headquartered in Saint-Josse-Ten-Noode, Bruxelles-Capitale and currently employs 1 full-time employees. The firm sales properties, rights relating to a property lease agreements, participation in the partnerships or subsidiaries which opted for that scheme. The properties owns by the Company are located in France and include buildings, hotels and residential spaces, among others.

Aquila SA is a France-based company that provides 24-hour security services. The Company specializes in the prevention and assistance services for corporate clients and private individuals. It offers interventions in the response to security alerts, accompaniment services for workmen and maintenance technicians in the locations where there may be a security risk, as well as intervention services for elderly people. In addition, the Company develops and markets security devices, notably its Aquimobil portable global positioning system (GPS) security alert device. As of December 31, 2010 Aquila SA operated two subsidiaries: 95%-owned Aquiserv SAS, focused on services for professionals and 98.92%-owned Aquimedia SARL, operating as a 24/24 hour call center.

Cofidur SA engages in electronic sub-contracting services. The company is headquartered in Nogent-Sur-Marne, Ile-De-France and currently employs 402 full-time employees. The firm operates through electronic manufacturing services and the design and production of printed circuits. Its products are used in such sectors as aviation technology and defense, multimedia and networks, transport, telecommunications and industry. Cofidur SA is a major shareholder of three companies: Cofidur EMS SA, Cofidur Electronique SA and Techci Rhone Alpes SA. Two of these, Cofidur EMS SA and Cofidur Electronique, are specialists in card and product integration. The third manufactures printed circuits. Through its holdings, the Company has a presence in various locations in France, Tunisia, Shanghai, Hong Kong and the United States.

Societa Editoriale Il Fatto SpA is an Italy-based media company. It manages different kind of media channels, such as the newspaper Il Fatto Quotidiano, a Website, a blog and Il fatto TV, an online television covering a wide range of topics both locally and globally. It also manages an electronic shop, which sells books, e-book and gadgets, among other.

American Shared Hospital Services engages in leasing radiosurgery and radiation therapy equipment to healthcare providers. The company is headquartered in San Francisco, California and currently employs 9 full-time employees. The firm provides Gamma Knife services through its over 81% indirect interest in GK Financing, LLC (GKF). The firm's business is the outsourcing of stereotactic radiosurgery services and radiation therapy services. The firm provides the equipment, as well as planning, installation, reimbursement and marketing support services. The firm's radiation therapy business consists of one Image Guided Radiation Therapy Operations (IGRT) system. IGRT technology integrates imaging and detection components into a linear accelerator, allowing clinicians to plan treatment, verify positioning and deliver treatment with a single device, providing radiation therapy with less damage to healthy tissue. The company is also engaged in proton beam radiation therapy business (PBRT).

TXCom SA designs, manufactures and markets communication products. The company is headquartered in Plessis-Robinson, Ile-De-France and currently employs 37 full-time employees. The firm specializes in radio transmission data devices and its product range includes radio frequency (RF) terminals, wireless scanners, such as hand held bar code scanners, transmission modems, vehicle-mounted terminals and Bluetooth Wifi PDAs. TXCOM SA provides solutions in various industry sectors, including automobile, cosmetic, food processing, as well as in retail, logistics and transport, among others. In addition, it offers maintenance and technical support services. TXCOM SA operates through its subsidiary companies, including Attel Ingenierie and AXIOHM USA.

Encres Dubuit SA produces and sells ultraviolet and solvent inks. The company is headquartered in Mitry-Mory, Ile-De-France and currently employs 182 full-time employees. The company offers a range of products, including ultraviolet (UV) polymerization inks and special varnishes, inks for the application on various materials and printing supplies. The firm supplies clients in four areas: Industry, New Technologies, Graphic and Label. The firm operates through its group companies, including SCREEN MESH, TINTAS DUBUIT, DUBUIT PAINT, DUBUIT Digital, DUBUIT Canada, QUEBEC INC, Encres DUBUIT SHANGHAI, DUBUIT BENELUX, PUBLIVENOR, ALL INKS, DUBUIT Shanghai Co and DUBUIT OF AMERICA. The firm has operations in Americas, Europe, Asia, Africa and Middle East.

Methanor SCA is a France-based company which is involved in anaerobic digestion industry. Anaerobic digestion is a natural process of transformation of organic matter. The Company uses this fermentation to produce renewable energy, biogas, which is used for electricity generation. The Company’s purpose is to limit greenhouse gas emissions and to transit from fossil fuels to renewable energies. It also funds agricultural biogas plants and enhances the production of biogas process. Methanor SCA also offers it’s investors a secure return with a visibility of 15 years.

Adomos SA is a France-based company that specializes in the provision of brokerage services to individuals investing in real estate via Internet. The Company offers its services directly via its dedicated Website and indirectly via partnerships with various banks and financial service companies. The Company operates through its two direct subsidiaries: Acheter-Louer.fr SA, which manages the Website www.acheter-louer.fr, devoted to online real estates operations, and Selectaux SAS, which provides online mortgage brokerage services. Adomos SA has also indirect subsidiary, Editions Paris Immobilier SARL, which is a specialist in selling space for real estate advertisement on Paris intra muros.

RocTool SA engages in the design and development of processes for transforming and molding composite materials. The company is headquartered in Le Bourget-Du-Lac, Auvergne-Rhone-Alpes and currently employs 32 full-time employees. The firm develops several processing technologies, such as the Cage System, an inductive heating process, which is a patented molding technology that heats tool surface by induction, as well as conventional composite processes, including resin transfer molding (RTM), thermo compression and thermoplastic injection, among others. Roctool SA cooperates with a number of manufacturers and material providers from such sectors as automotive, sport and leisure, and aircraft. The firm offers licenses of its patents to companies in many different markets, comprising automotive and transportation, construction and medical equipment.

Horizontal Software SA designs and develops software solutions for time and notifications management. The company is headquartered in Lomme, Hauts-De-France and currently employs 89 full-time employees. The firm focuses on developing and commercializing a horizontal software platform that enables complete human resources (HR) management. The platform is distributed in software as a service (SaaS) mode and cloud architecture, as well as application mode. Its options includes e-recruitment, interviews analysis, employees data administration, browsing candidates profiles, analysis of custom HR factors, such as teams activity, absences and trainings, processing of payroll, validation of medical documentation, time management, as well as planning and optimization of HR resources, among others.

Enertime SA provides solutions for electricity generation technology, using organic rankine cycle modules. The company is headquartered in Courbevoie, Ile-De-France and currently employs 25 full-time employees. The firm is an engineering and consulting firm that focuses on renewable energy strategies, engineering work for investors as owners engineer for bio-energy project such as Biosmass and Biogas, promotion and development of solar energy and bio-energy. Enertime designs, builds and runs its own Organic Rankine Cycle modules or ORCs, for power generation without CO2. The firm's main project concerns photovoltaic solar power plants on hazardous lands, boilers or biomass power plants using difficult-to-burn biomass (straw, poultry litter, spent wash, etc. ), non-conventional thermodynamic cycles (negative cold production). Moreover, the Company designs turbines specially adapted to clients needs and project specifications..

Neovacs SA is a biotechnology company which engages in the development of active immunotherapies for treating auto-immune, inflammatory, and cancerous diseases. The company is headquartered in Paris, Ile-De-France and currently employs 24 full-time employees. The company specializes in immunotherapy domain and providing treatment for autoimmune and inflammatory diseases. The firm researches and develops Kinoids, drug-candidates which aim to treat disease by including an antibody response in the patient. The firm focuses its development effort on two Kinoids for Crohn’s disease, Rheumatoid Arthritis and lupus disease. Neovacs SA’s portfolio of products includes TNF-Kinoids, IFN-Kinoids and VEGF-Kinoids. The firm operates in France and the United States. In May 2016, the Company signed a joint venture agreement with Stellar Biotechnologies Inc to create Neostell, owned by the Company in 70%.

AwoX SA engages in the design and development of electronic devices and smart home technologies. The company is headquartered in Montpellier, Occitanie and currently employs 102 full-time employees. AwoX's products and solutions are used in products such as televisions, decoders, personal computers as others. The firm's core activity focuses on developing software and electronic products for license to consumer electronics manufacturers. Based on Universal Plug and Play (UPnP) and DLNA standards, the modular AwoX architecture helps manufacturers add network functionality to their own products by adapting AwoX's reference hardware design, customizing the AwoX internationalized user interface, and developing new plug-ins. AwoX uses its technologies to develop software and electronic products for the consumer market.

Lexibook Linguistic Electronic System SA engages in designing and marketing of consumer pocket-sized electronic products. The company is headquartered in Les Ulis, Ile-De-France and currently employs 64 full-time employees. The firm offers a range of products, including toys, calculators, dictionaries translators, computers, tablets, clocks, weather clocks, telephones, among others. The company also offers electronic educational toys and games. The firm sells the products under more than 200 brands, including Barbie, Disney, Furby, among others. The firm markets the products in more than 40 countries and is present in France, the United Kingdom, Germany, Spain, Hong Kong, Portugal and Italy, among others. As of December 31, 2013, the Company had three of subsidiaries: Lexibook Hong Kong Ltd, Lexibook Spain SL and Lexibook United States.

AdUX SA engages in the website publishing with Hi-Media Publishing; audience monetization for its own sites and for third-party sites through online advertising via its Hi-Media Advertising network and content monetization via its division Hi-Media Payments with its micro-payment platform, Allopass and its e-wallet, Hipay. The company is headquartered in Levallois-Perret, Ile-De-France and currently employs 136 full-time employees. The firm operates through two business divisions: Publishers division and Advertisers Solutions. Publishers division specializes in the publishing of Websites, including Fotolog.com, Jeuxvideo.com, Blogorama.fr, Actustar.com, MagicRPM.com, GameOnly.com and Mujeractual.com. Advertisers division provides advertising sales and direct marketing services under the Hi-Media Network brand, and also offers electronic payment services under the brand names Allopass (micropayment platform), Hipay (electronic wallet) and Mobile Trend (mobile marketing and SMS center). The company offers its services in France, Germany, Spain, Portugal, China and the United States, among others. The firm has subsidiaries as Admoove, a French location-based mobile advertising company, among others.

Dietswell is engaged in the provision of engineering and drilling services to oil and gas industries. The company is headquartered in Guyancourt, Ile-De-France and currently employs 37 full-time employees. The firm specializes in the design, drilling, work-over and completion engineering. The company offers well engineering services, such as well engineering, preparation and evaluation of tenders, offset wells reviews; drilling project management, management of the stock of spare parts, supply of communications and logistic support, among others; drilling contracting; rig design and contracting, which designs, constructs and refurbish rigs; rig inspection and audits, which provide customized inspection and audit services; and provision of technical assistance. Dietswell SA principally provides its services to ageing oilfields that need updating, or that need to be decommissioned in an environmentally friendly manner. The firm holds stakes in two companies: Dolfines Logistique and Feumag Holding Company Limited. In October 2013, it announced the creation of Dietswell Brazil.

EO2 engages in the wood energy sector. The company is headquartered in Malakoff, Ile-De-France and currently employs 35 full-time employees. The company produces wood pellets used as a biofuel for individual, collective and industrial heating systems (boiler, stove etc.). The wood pellets are made from sawdust and wood shavings, which are dried, pressed and cut in order to obtain a cylindrical shaped granule. The Company’s production sites are located in the Auvergne and the Landes regions of France. The firm sells its products throughout France via a network of distributors.

Ober SA engages in the design, manufacturing and marketing of decorative wood panels. The company is headquartered in Longeville En Barrois, Grand Est and currently employs 430 full-time employees. The firm markets and distributes a range of real wood veneered panels for decorative and acoustic use under the Oberflex brand name. Its product range includes ready-to-bond laminates, such as wood laminates with the Oberflex finish, unfinished wood laminates, decorative laminates and edge banding; ready-to-use wood products, including ready-to-use customized and standard wood panels; jointed wood panels for boat decking, including deck d'Ober; ceiling solutions, including ready-to-use customized and standard ceiling solutions, and tiles for raised flooring. The company also offers technical and commercial back-up services to its customers. Its products are used by hotels, schools, medical centers, restaurants and sports clubs. Ober SA operates through Concrete LCDA, Marotte SAS and Stramiflex.

Groupe Parot SA engages in the sales and distribution of automobiles. The company is headquartered in Bruges, Nouvelle-Aquitaine. The firm is a new car dealer. The company offers passenger's cars and trucks. The firm operates through Societe Behra Holding SAS, a Puteaux-based new car dealer and Brienne Auto.

Klimvest Plc engages in the development and distribution of software solutions. The firm's segments include Canada, United Kingdom, Germany, Switzerland, US, Denmark, Ireland, Spain, France, South Africa and Netherlands. The firm's business operations include the provision of change management and education support services for companies undergoing business or technological change; the licensing of change management and education support software, and the ongoing maintenance of the software solutions licensed to companies. The firm's products include Vimago, Vimago Train, Vimago Assist, Vimago Analyse and Vimago Collaborate. The firm's professional services include project management, organizational change management, technical consulting and toolset support.

Avalon Holdings Corp. engages in the provision of waste management services to industrial, commercial, municipal, and governmental customers. The company is headquartered in Warren, Ohio and currently employs 388 full-time employees. The firm operates through two segments. The firm's waste management services segment includes waste disposal brokerage and management services, captive landfill management operations and salt water injection well operations. The golf and related operations segment includes the operation and management of over three golf courses and related clubhouses, a hotel, fitness centers, tennis courts, spa services, dining and banquet and conference facilities and a travel agency. Its subsidiary, American Waste Management Services, Inc., assists customers with managing and disposing of wastes at various treatment and disposal sites. Its golf courses are located in Warren, Ohio, Vienna, Ohio and Sharon, Pennsylvania.

Avenir Telecom SA engages in the distribution and retail of telephone products and services. The company is headquartered in Marseille, Paca and currently employs 201 full-time employees. The company supplies individual and corporate clients with mobile phones and accessories, multimedia equipment, as well as telephone subscriptions. The firm owns a network of numerous stores, under the Internity brand name, which offers a range of mobile telephones, digital imagery devices, games and accessories. The company also provides its products through Mobile Hut, a network multi-operator retailer offering prepaid sales, post-paid subscriptions and renewal offers. In addition, the Company serves its customers through independent retailers, specialty distribution, hypermarkets and other distribution channels. Avenir Telecom SA operates various subsidiaries, including Voxland, Ensitel Lojas de Comunicacoes SA, Avenir Telecom Romania Ltd, Avenir Telecom Espagne and Fintelco SGPS, among others.

Mastrad SA engages in the design, manufacture, and distribution of kitchen utensils and appliances. The company is headquartered in Paris, Ile-De-France and currently employs 28 full-time employees. The firm offers over 350 products, marketed in the product ranges, including preparation, which is comprised of oven mitts and vegetable peelers; cooking range, which includes cooking forks, dishes and baking trays; timing and measurement range, which includes timers, scales and thermometers; baking and desserts range, which includes pastry torches and cake pans; kids serving items; straining items, barware and beverage, which includes corkscrews and ice cube trays; utensils range, which includes spatulas, whisks and scrapers; barbeque holders; recipe books and cooking utensils, including pans, steamers and forms, among others. In October, 2013, the Company completed the merger of its subsidiary Kitchen Bazaar with TOC, creating CETOC, in which the Company holds a 44% stake.

Emova Group SA engages in retail and distribution of flowers and decorative plants. The company is headquartered in Paris, Ile-De-France and currently employs 85 full-time employees. The company offers a range of cut flowers, blooming and green plants available in flower shops in nine countries, including France, Spain, Italy, Belgium, Germany, Japan and others. The firm's network comprises more than 450 flower shops, operating under Monceu Fleurs, Happy and Rapi'Flore brands. The company also develops franchise agreements with flower sellers. The firm operates through its subsidiaries, including Happy Inc., La Generale des Vegetaux, Flore Distribution, KSV, Global Export, Gestflore, Floria Creation SAS, Hauraunize, Monceau Fleurs International and Monceau Fleurs, among others.

AdThink SA provides online platform for advertiser and clients. The company is headquartered in Tassin-La-Demi-Lune, Auvergne-Rhone-Alpes and currently employs 152 full-time employees. The company focuses on two complementary spheres of activities: Adthink Monetization division, operating through subsidiaries, Profiles Partner and Click Medias, offering Internet services, micro payment facility through Internet and performance marketing services and Adthink Publishing division, operating through subsidiaries, Numerik Art, It News Info and Keep Traffic, offering software publishing services, Internet games and maintaining Traffic Generation Sphere. The company operates through other subsidiaries, including wholly owned Advertstream and partially owned Miss Good Buy. Apart from France, the Company also operates in the United States.

ENENSYS Technologies designs and manufactures professional equipment and software enabling efficient video delivery over broadcast & telecom networks. The company is headquartered in Cesson-Sevigne, Bretagne and currently employs 64 full-time employees. The firm specializes in the broadcast of digital television via mobile telephones using digital video broadcasting, including handheld (DVB-H) and terrestrial digital multimedia broadcasting (T-DMB) technologies, among others. The company also manufactures digital television/information technology interfacing solutions. The firm's core products include baseband converters, network adapters and Peripheral Component Interconnect (PCI) card adapters, among others.

I.Céram SA engages in the development, manufacture and sale of orthopedic implants and instruments. The company is headquartered in Limoges, Nouvelle-Aquitaine and currently employs 40 full-time employees. The company offers implants for various body parts, produced of metal, polymer and ceramic. The firm has own laboratory and researchers developing a range of bone fillers.

Acheter-Louer.fr SA provides information on real estate activities through advertisements in journals and the internet. The company is headquartered in Les Ulis, Ile-De-France and currently employs 27 full-time employees. Marketing services are provided through online Internet sites, distribution of free publications, production of institutional brochures, announcements, and through free announcement newspapers. Through its Website www.acheter-louer.fr, the Company offers different search options, such as type, price and location, and the announcement consist of a portfolio of photographs. The company also diffuses magazines, such as Acheter-louer.fr, Actua Immo and Paris Immobilier. In addition, the Company is engaged in the field of marketing communication consulting and other services.

Prismaflex International SA manufactures billboards and digital screens. The company is headquartered in Haute-Rivoire, Auvergne-Rhone-Alpes and currently employs 385 full-time employees. The firm provides outdoor signs, including trivision signs displaying three advertising campaigns, street furniture like bus shelters, display columns and city lights, scrolling signs, LED signs and traditional signs. The company also offers indoor and outdoor point-of-purchase advertisings like printed carpets, light boxes, hanging systems, printed self-adhesives, parking billboards, movie frames and window solutions, among others used for trade fairs, exhibitions, festivals and other events. The firm also offers digital printing services designed for Prismaflex displays. The company markets substrates, inks and other materials used in printing industry. The company operates through subsidiaries based in Canada, the United States, the United Kingdom, Spain, France, South Africa, Bahrain, Australia, Sweden and the Russian Federation.

Makheia Group SA creates and develops solutions for communication media. The company is headquartered in Paris, Ile-De-France and currently employs 15 full-time employees. The firm's activities are divided into three divisions: the Corporate division, which regroups the agencies Sequoia, Franklin Partners and Makheia Corporate, and specializes in internal, corporate and financial communication, brand strategy and institutional advertising; the Marketing Services division, which includes the agencies Makheia Affinity and Place du Marche, and specializes in operational and relationship marketing as well as brand design and identity; and the Collaborative Solutions division with Makheia Mediamanagement, which provides solutions such as editorial platforms, marketing campaign management and production automation. The company operates through La Deuxieme Maison Agency and Les Argonautes SAS, among others. The company joins Mademoiselle Scarlett advertising agency.

i2S SA designs, manufactures and distributes cameras and optronic system. The company is headquartered in Pessac, Nouvelle-Aquitaine and currently employs 68 full-time employees. The company operates through its divisions, including i2S Digibook, which designs, manufactures and markets a range of scanners and related software for the digitization of ancient books, bound documents and archives, i2S Vision, which offers digital vision solutions and remote transmission cameras and i2S OEM Devices, which takes care of the development from prototype to mass production of dedicated vision systems. The range of Company’s products includes smart cameras, digital scanners, specialized opto-electronics and image processing software and embedded analysis. The firm's clients are government organizations, libraries, archives, museums, service providers, scientific and university organizations, as well as equipment manufacturers, among others. I2S SA operates through its subsidiary, i2S Inc, located in the United States and other dependant companies.

Adeunis RF SA designs, manufactures and markets sensors and wireless solutions for the operational performance of professionals. The company is headquartered in Crolles, Auvergne-Rhone-Alpes. The scope of activity of the Company cover areas such as temperature monitoring, state reporting, transmitting, general packet radio service (GPRS) data management and network tracking solutions, among many others. The company products include Dry Contacts, which reports states 0-1 and control relays; Temp, which measures both internal and external temperatures; Analog & Analog PWR, which gives IOT connectivity to wired sensors; Pulse, which enables counters to communicate; Modbus, which tests one or more MODBUS slaves; Ambient Sensor, which controls temperature rise; Repeater, which Expands network capacity, and Receiver, which collects data from transmitters, among others.

AND International Publishers NV engages in the provision of digital maps and location-based services. The company is headquartered in Capelle Aan Den Ijssel, Zuid-Holland and currently employs 80 full-time employees. The firm offers road database that connects over 200 countries in the world, including fully attributed navigation maps of Western Europe. The firm offers Navigation Maps, which are suitable for turn-by-turn navigation and Location Based Services; Digital Maps, which are optimized for route planning, time-distance calculations and optimization studies, and Geocoding Maps, which are suitable for (reverse) geocoding, address verification and includes all streets and house number (ranges). The Company’s digital maps are used for navigation and mapping; location based services; advertising and marketing; mobile resource management and geographic information system, and government.

madvertise SA is engaged in the provision of digital marketing solutions. The company is headquartered in Boulogne-Billancourt, Ile-De-France and currently employs 67 full-time employees. The company operates three business divisions: Mobile advertising network division with Mbrand3, a mobile advertising network and M-Perf, a pay-for-performance mobile advertising network; Technical and consulting agency division with Bemobee, a mobile consulting company that specializes in the design, development and promotion of mobile applications and Nemo Agency, a mobile marketing agency that focuses on consulting, design of sites, and mobile application and the generation of traffic and performance measurement on mobile technologies; and Publication division with avec Baobab Entertainment, a mobile publisher that offers an entertainment content on mobile devices. The company has such subsidiaries as Madvertise, among others.

Augros Cosmetics Packaging SA designs, manufactures, and markets packaging materials. The company is headquartered in Cerise, Normandie and currently employs 206 full-time employees. The company produces moldings for cosmetics of such brands as Nivea, Hugo, Clarins, Soul, Star, Burberry and Emporio, among others. The products include mainly glass and plastic bottles, cardboard packages, perfume bottles, makeup compacts and containers. The technical solutions used in manufacturing are the packaging materials, including silk screen printing, lacquering, varnishing, dual injection, ultrasonic welding and metallization, among others. The firm focuses the activities on luxury packaging, conducted by two plants in Alencon, and decoration on plastic and glass, carried out in Le Theil sur Huisne. As of December 31, 2013 the Company had no subsidiaries.

Alumexx NV engages in the production of aluminum climbing materials for DIY, painting and maintenance work at height.. The company is headquartered in Etten-Leur, Noord-Brabant and currently employs 14 full-time employees. The firm's products include ladders, stepladders and scaffolds. They are marketed at the do-it-yourself market in Europe and North America, with client base consisting of private and semi-professional users. The firm works with a dealer network in the Netherlands, as well as operates its own distribution center and an online store.

AP Alternative Assets, L.P. (AAA) is a closed-end limited partnership whose partners include AAA Guernsey Limited (the Managing General Partner), which holds approximately 100% of the general partner interests in AAA, and the holders of common units representing limited partner interests in AAA. Its investment mandate is to invest substantially all of its capital in Apollo-sponsored entities, funds and private equity transactions. Its portfolio consists of a single opportunistic investment in the economic equity of Athene Holding Ltd. (Athene Holding). Through its subsidiaries, Athene Holding provides insurance products focused primarily on the retirement market and its business focuses on issuing or reinsuring fixed indexed annuities. The products and services offered by Athene Holding include reinsurance services offered to third-party annuity providers, and institutional products, such as funding agreements. AAA is managed by Apollo Alternative Assets, L.P.

Fashion B Air SA is a France-based company specialized in the design and marketing of ready-to-wear women's clothing and accessories like shoes and bags. It operates boutiques in Paris, in St Germain en Laye, Bordeaux and Lille, and sells its products also in shopping malls in France, such as Galeries Lafayette and Printemps Haussmann. In addition, the Company's offer is available via its Website, www.belair-paris.fr. Fashion B Air SA also operates through subsidiaries, including Vertigo, which reported no activities and Les Florentines, which operates through the brand 40 CARATS and which is engaged in the correspondence sale of jewels, textiles and phytotherapy products, such as capillary products, food supplements, anti-fatigue products, and engaged in the distribution of fine and costume jewelry.

Planet Media SA publishes internet news. The company is headquartered in Paris, Ile-De-France and currently employs 35 full-time employees. The Website www.seniorplanet.fr is an Internet portal specifically tailored to the interests of senior citizens (people over 50). The portal contains news, lifestyle and general interest articles. The company has a number of broad sections, including Money & Law, Health, Employment & Retirement, Environment, High Tech, Genealogy, Family and Travel, among others. The Website also provides weather forecasts, news headlines, and a variety of chat rooms and forums, as well as advertising links to products and services. The firm also operates the Website www.femmesplus.fr, which is intended for women over 35, www.medisite.fr, a medical information portal and www.planetgolf.fr.

Ordissimo SA is a France-based company active in the computer hardware industry. The Company is a manufacturer and a wholesaler of electronic computers and other equipments. The Company offers different product lines such as, computers, which includes tablets, laptops and mini-towers; smartphones; accessories, such as keyboards and external hard disks; services, which includes products guarantee and online computer educational services; books, which includes special books for learning computer skills and printers. Ordissimo offers its products online and in different point of sales all around French territory.

Cerinnov Group SA engages in the design, manufacturing, and marketing of production and decorating solutions for the ceramics and glass sectors. The company is headquartered in Limoges, Nouvelle-Aquitaine and currently employs 136 full-time employees. The firm offers various types of machines, which are used in various stages of production of ceramics. Cerinnov Group SA's portfolio of machines includes laser machines, shaping and glazing machines, decration machines, customized machines, consumables and after sales - second hand equipment. The firm is present in worldwide, with subsidiaries in France, United Kingdom, Germany and United States.

Logic Instrument SA manufactures, designs, and supplies outdoor smartphones, rugged laptop, and tablets. The company is headquartered in Igny, Ile-De-France and currently employs 34 full-time employees. The firm's products are used in such applications as the maintenance and programming of robots in factories, wireless data transmission, military signal analysis, telecommunication protocol analysis and simulation, as well as high-speed video image acquisition and others. The product range include fieldbook, GETAC computers, rugged convertible PCs, PXI & PXIe portable, ruggedized outdoor handhelds and military & industrial display solutions, among others. The company supplies customers in the telecommunication, broadcasting, insurance, medical research, car manufacturing, military and avionics sectors, among others. Logic Instrument SA operates through its two wholly owned subsidiaries, Logic Instrument Inc, based in the United States and Logic Instrument GmbH, based in Germany.

Vialife SA engages in online press. The company is headquartered in Paris, Ile-De-France and currently employs 31 full-time employees. Through its Website, www.viapresse.com, the Company offers subscription deals for over 500 various French publications and nearly 4,000 titles in retail. The firm's offering comprises popular and specialist magazines, newspapers and periodicals, as well as professional and trade journals, among others. Viapresse SA provides its services to individuals and corporate clients and operates delivery in France and abroad.

ASIT BioTech SA is a clinical stage biopharmaceutical company, which engages in the research and development of immunotherapy treatments for environmental and food allergies. The company is headquartered in Liege, Liege and currently employs 20 full-time employees.

long name: Nexponor Sociedade Especial de Investimento Imobiliario de Capital Fixo SICAFI SA
description: Nexponor Sociedade Especial de Investimento Imobiliario de Capital Fixo Sicafi SA (Nexponor SICAFI) is a Portugal-based collective investment fund. Nexponor Sociedade Especial de Investimento Imobiliario de Capital Fixo Sicafi SA focuses on the investment in real estate segment. Its medium and long-term investment objective is to provide shareholder returns through investing in a diversified urban real estate portfolio in Continental Europe with the potential for income and capital growth. Nexponor Sociedade Especial de Investimento Imobiliario de Capital Fixo Sicafi SA focuses on the establishment and management of a portfolio. Its major shareholder is Fund Box Sociedade Gestora de Fundos de Investimento Imobiliario SA.

description: Bernard Loiseau SA engages in the operation of hotels and restaurants. The company is headquartered in Saulieu, Bourgogne-Franche-Comte and currently employs 64 full-time employees. The firm operates two restaurants in Paris, Tante Louise and Tante Marguerite. The company also operates Relais Bernard Loiseau, a hotel, restaurant and spa complex in Saulieu, Burgundy, and Loiseau des Vignes, a restaurant in Beaune. The firm operates through its subsidiaries, such as Loiseau des Vignes SA, Chez Tante Louise SAS, Chez Marius SA, SCI Du Maine, Au Pays de Bresse SARL and BL Organisation EURL. Bernard Loiseau SA has also established partnerships with Manotel Group for the provision of consulting services, including support in designing menus and training staff of Manotel hotels and with Agis SA for the creation of a line of fresh prepared dishes (vacuum-packed) that are sold by retail outlets. Bernard Loiseau SA has also entered into contracts of partnerships with Gabriel Boudier, Albert Bichot, Edmond Fallot and Societe immobiliere du Maine.

Spineguard SA engages in the design and manufacture of medical devices for the spine. The company is headquartered in Vincennes, Ile-De-France and currently employs 19 full-time employees. The firm offers PediGuard, a handheld wireless device that is used to detect possible cortex perforation during pedicle preparation for screw placement. There are three varieties of the product: Classic PediGuard; Curved PediGuard, which has a curved gearshift, and Cannulated PediGuard, which has a cannulated shaft.

AeroCentury Corp. engages in the business of investing in used regional aircraft equipment leased to foreign and domestic regional air carriers. The company is headquartered in Burlingame, California and currently employs 11 full-time employees. The firm's segment is leasing of regional aircraft to foreign and domestic regional airlines. The business of the Company is managed by JetFleet Management Corp. (JMC), an integrated aircraft management, marketing and financing business. JMC is a subsidiary of JetFleet Holding Corp (JHC). The firm has been engaged in the business of investing in used regional aircraft equipment leased to foreign and domestic regional air carriers. The firm owns regional aircraft and engines, which are leased to customers under triple net leases with terms that are less than the useful life of the assets. The firm's aircraft and aircraft engines that were on lease or held for lease includes turboprop aircraft, regional jet aircraft and engines.

Gold by Gold SA engages in trading, mining, and refining precious metals. The company is headquartered in Paris, Ile-De-France and currently employs 5 full-time employees. The Company‘s activities include Trading, Collection & Recycling and Refining & Recycling. The processed products are resold primarily to the jewelry industry. Trading includes buying gold in Latin America and selling gold in Europe. The Collection & Recycling division deals with purchasing and recycling precious metals from individuals as well as from businesses. The Refining and Recycling division collects the gold via their website and it is refined and resold. Silver, platinum and palladium are also refined. The firm also offers technical expertise services, financing services, and logistical services to miners. The company operates through two France-based subsidiaries: Aurfina Sarl and Bon Aloi Sas and one affiliate Jel Sarl.

BD Multimédia SA engages in the provision of telecommunication services. The company is headquartered in Paris, Ile-De-France and currently employs 30 full-time employees. The firm specializes in two main areas: Payment Services, which includes micropayment, electronic commerce, prepaid bank cards, and Community Services. Its product portfolio includes StarPass, which includes a number of payment solutions; Toneo First, which is a prepaid rechargeable payment card launched in partnership with Mastercard, and Payment.net, which is an online payment processing platform regardless of the channel, including web or mobile allowing the sale of digital content or physical goods. Apart from France, BD Multi Media SA is present in Oceania, Thailand, Vietnam, Indonesia, Malaysia, Brazil and Mexico. Its subsidiaries include BD Multimedia Hong-Kong Ltd, Paycom, Gayplanet and Distkoo, among others.

Immersion SA engages in the importation and sale of technology products in France, which are unobtainable in the territory, to meet the needs of industry pioneers in the use of virtual reality. The company is headquartered in Bordeaux, Nouvelle-Aquitaine. The firm's team design immersive spaces for digital templates and virtual prototypes, as well as for reviewing projects and simulation for the purposes of evaluating issues. The firm specializes in four areas of expertise, such as State of the Art, Innovation and Research and Development (R&D), Immersive Three Dimensional (3D) Solutions, and 3i Solutions. Immersion SA designs Its solutions for all markets, such as aerospace, automotive, shipbuilding, transportation, defense, architecture, construction, energy, industrial equipment, health, education, research, among others.

Oxatis SA is a France-based company that provides e-commerce solutions. The Company develops an e-commerce solution that integrates software, hosting and support capabilities for businesses to create and operate their own personalized online commerce Website. In addition, the Company also offers Web design services, online product referencing services, e-commerce consulting services, users can select a preferred protocol, benefit from technical support and backward compatibility, among others. The tools provided by the Company allow users to respond to the requests of clients and use a customized language and framework to develop autonomously. Oxatis SA offers its services in France, as well as in Spain, Switzerland, Belgium, Italy, the United Kingdom and Canada.

Implanet SA is a France-based company. It is involved in the design, production and marketing of medical equipment, such as medical implants and devices used in orthopedic surgery. The Company's products include prosthetic knees, spinal bracing systems, intersomatic cages, pins, suture threads, screws and anchors, among others. Its brands portfolio includes Spine System and Jazz. The Implanet Spine System aims to provide immobilization and stabilization of the spinal segments in skeletally mature patients as an adjunct to fusion of the thoracic, lumbar and sacral spine. The Implanet Jazz System, its flagship product, is an implant used to improve the treatment of spinal conditions requiring vertebral fusion.

Douaisienne de Basse Tension SAS distributes energy solutions. The company is headquartered in Brebieres, Hauts-De-France and currently employs 79 full-time employees. The firm provides electric and water distribution units, including up to 12 x 16A single phase outlets and up to 4 water distribution taps, recharging units and boxes for electrical vehicles and retractable access control bollards and deterrent systems. The firm also manufactures electric current transformers for domestic and industrial use. Douaisienne de Basse Tension SAS has a network of distribution agents in France, Belgium, the Netherlands and Sweden. In 2011, the Company launched its US subsidiary, DBT USA.

Entreparticuliers.com SA operates as a website for the buy and sell of real estate properties between private individuals. The company is headquartered in Paris, Ile-De-France and currently employs 66 full-time employees. The clients use the Website to advertise their property for sale or rental. The firm's Website also provides links to online property financing companies, legal advisers, household removals agencies and other property-related services. Entreparticuliers.com SA also produces a paper-based property newspaper, entitled Les Annonces Immobilieres.

Groupe Actiplay SA engages in marketing and e-marketing of online gaming operations. The company is headquartered in Bordeaux, Nouvelle-Aquitaine and currently employs 8 full-time employees. The firm controls the entire value chain from creation to the promotion of games. The firm develops games (technical implementation for all types of media Web, sms, audio, verifying accordance with French legislation) and ensures promotion through its support media, including the Web.

Spineway SA is engaged in the design, production, and sale of spinal column implants and surgical instruments. The company is headquartered in Ecully, Auvergne-Rhone-Alpes and currently employs 35 full-time employees. The company designs, produces and sells spinal column implants and surgical instruments. The group offers spinal systems, cervical and lumbar cages, cervical plates, bone substitutes, among others.

Groupimo SA provides integrated real estate services. The company is headquartered in Fort-De-France, Martinique and currently employs 39 full-time employees. The company provides asset administration services, co-ownership management services, real estate management services, leasing management services, transaction services, as well as insurance brokerage and financing services. As of December 31, 2010, Groupimo SA operates through its 25 subsidiaries, including Comaphi SARL, Lesage SARL, MI Marin SARL, Marina de Baie Mahault SARL and Mantout. The firm operates in France, Martinique, Guadeloupe, Guyana and Saint Martin.

Si Participations SCA, formerly Siparex Croissance SCA, is a France-based independent private equity investment and asset management company, primarily dedicated to growth capital and mid-market buy-out/buy-in financing. The companies and funds managed by the Company are primarily in the commerce and distribution, consulting, chemical and pharmaceuticals, metal works sectors, electrical and electronicengineering and construction, among others. The Company has operations in France, Europe and the United States.

Safe Orthopaedics SA is a France-based company principally engaged in the medical devices industry. The Company focuses on the development and commercialization of products for use in spinal surgery. It provides a range of implants and ready to use instrument kits. The Company's product portfolio comprises SteriSpine PS, which is the Pedicle Screw System; and SteriSpine LC, which is the Lumbar Cage System that enables safe implant positioning, as well as access, insertion and placement of the implant. The Company's products are equipped with quick change handle, dual trial and impact removal, among others. The Company mainly uses polyarylamid material, which is a polymar with 50% glass fibers.

César SA engages in the design, manufacturing, and marketing of party items. The company is headquartered in Saumur, Pays De La Loire and currently employs 552 full-time employees. The firm produces costumes, masks, paper deco products, wigs, panoplies, make-up items, toys and accessories. The company markets and sells its products through distributors, including retailers and wholesalers.

Cybergun SA is a France-based company which designs and distributes replica dummy weapons for video games, sport or outdoor shooting and collectors. Made from either plastic or metal, the Company's soft air guns are exact replicas of products from firearm manufacturers. Its soft air guns are intended for use in leisure and sports and require protective glasses. The Company manufactures soft air-gun replicas of a wide range of firearm brands, including Smith & Wesson, Firepower, Kalashnikov, Fames, Uzi, Sig Sauer, Mauser and Galil. The Company's soft air guns are mainly distributed in arms shops and fishing and hunting shops. It is also operational through its wholly owned subsidiaries, Microtrade, Interactive Game Group, Cybergun Italy SRL, among others, and via indirect subsidiaries, including Cybergun International SA, Cybergun USA, Softair USA Inc., Palco Sports, Asgun Doo, Cybergun Hong Kong, Tech Group HK, among others.

Evadix SA is a Belgium-based holding company primarily engaged in business support services such as printing, direct marketing and logistics services. The Company is engaged in printing and offers digital pre-press, large-format digital transfer to film, offset printing on rotary presses and on sheet-fed presses and binding services. It also focuses on direct marketing and provides services, such as computer processing and data management, customized laser and inkjet printing, preparation for mailing and film wrapping. The Company's another activity is logistics, which supplies various services, such as warehouse management, order preparation and supply chain management. Evadix SA operates through a number of subsidiaries in Belgium, including EVADIX Bilog SA, EVADIX.

Methorios Capital SpA is an Italy-based company primarily engaged in the strategic financial advice sector. The Company is an independent financial advisor specialized in corporate finance transactions. It operates at Italian and European market, with the aim to assist small and medium-sized businesses, providing them consulting services. It offers the advisory services on strategic investments in listed and unlisted companies, as well as advisory on the mobilization of assets. The Company divides its activities into three main sectors: Advisory, which includes consulting services on corporate finance, mergers and acquisitions, equity capital markets and debt corporate finance; Equity, which comprises direct investments in the risk capital of listed and private companies, and Structured Finance, which consists of factoring and credit purchase activities. As of December 31, 2011, the Company had three direct subsidiaries: MC Holding Srl, MC Eventi Srl and MC Real Estate Srl.

Toolux Sanding SA is a Luxembourg-based holding company engaged in the tool production sector. The Company specializes in the design, manufacture and sale of various kinds of hand tools for both professional and home use, including screwdrivers, pipe spanners and multipurpose spanners. Its products are distributed under Toolux brand and under distributors brand names (MDD), mainly in retail stores, such as Castorama in France and Home Depot in the United States among others.

Amoéba S.A. develops, produces, and sells biological biocides. It develops BIOMEBA, a biopesticide that harnesses the biocidal properties of Willaertia magna, which is used to treat cooling towers. The company was founded in 2010 and is headquartered in Chassieu, France.

AmeriCann, Inc. operates as a specialized cannabis company in the United States. It intends to design, develop, lease, and operate cultivation, processing, and manufacturing facilities for licensed cannabis businesses in the United States. The company was formerly known as Nevada Health Scan, Inc. and changed its name to AmeriCann, Inc. in 2014. AmeriCann, Inc. was founded in 2010 and is based in Denver, Colorado.

Aspirational Consumer Lifestyle Corp. focuses on effecting a merger, share exchange, asset acquisition, share purchase, reorganization or similar business combination with one or more businesses or entities. The company was founded in 2020 and is based in Singapore.

long name: Ashoka India Equity Investment Trust PLC
description: Ashoka India Equity Investment Trust PLC is an investment trust (the Trust). The Trust’s investment objective is to achieve long-term capital appreciation. It primarily invests in securities listed in India, and securities of companies with a presence in India. The Trust may also invest in unquoted companies with presence in India. White Oak Capital Management Consultants LLP is the Trust’s investment adviser.

description: AIQ Limited focuses on social commerce businesses comprising social media platforms. It primarily focuses on seeking opportunities in data mining, artificial intelligence technologies, and social and online media, such as instant messaging platforms, as well as in the e-commerce sector. The company was incorporated in 2017 and is headquartered in Grand Cayman, the Cayman Islands.

Artificial Intelligence Technology Solutions Inc. focuses on the delivery of artificial intelligence and robotic solutions for operational, security, and monitoring needs. The company was formerly known as On The Move Systems Corp. and changed its name to Artificial Intelligence Technology Solutions Inc. in August 2018. Artificial Intelligence Technology Solutions Inc. was founded in 2016 is based in Reno, Nevada.

Atlantica, Inc. does not have significant operations. The company intends to seek potential assets, property, or businesses to acquire, in a business combination, by reorganization, merger, or acquisition. Previously, it was involved in the real estate development business. The company was formerly known as Community Equities Corporation and changed its name to Atlantica, Inc. in March 1996. Atlantica, Inc. was founded in 1938 and is based in Hobe Sound, Florida.

Acorn Capital Investment Fund Limited is an open ended equity mutual fund launched and managed by Acorn Capital Limited. The fund invests in public equity markets of Australia. It invests in the listed and unlisted microcap companies. The fund benchmarks its performance against S&P/ASX Small Ordinaries Accumulation Index. It invests in the companies operating across diversified sectors. Acorn Capital Investment Fund Limited was launched in 2014 and is domiciled in Australia.

Amergent Hospitality Group, Inc. engages in owning, operating, and franchising of fast casual and full-service restaurants in the United States and Europe. The company owns and franchises 36 fast casual restaurants under the American Burger Company, The Burger Joint, and Little Big Burger names. It also operates a full-service restaurant under the Hooters name. Amergent Hospitality Group, Inc. is headquartered in Charlotte, North Carolina.

AmeraMex International, Inc. sells, leases, and rents new and refurbished heavy equipment primarily in the United States. The company's products are used in light and infrastructure construction, shipping logistics, mining, and commercial farming industries. It serves customers in the United States, Canada, Latin America, Asia, and Africa. The company was incorporated in 1989 and is based in Chico, California.

AF Legal Group Limited operates as a family and relationship law firm in Australia. It provides family law services, such as separation, divorce, child custody, child support, spousal maintenance, and property settlement. The company was formerly known as Navigator Resources Limited and changed its name to AF Legal Group Limited in May 2019. AF Legal Group Limited was incorporated in 1994 and is based in Melbourne, Australia.

ActivEX Limited engages in the acquisition, identification, and delineation of mineral resource projects. The company focuses on the exploration of gold, copper, and potash mineralization. It holds interests in 1 granted mining lease located in Western Australia; and 23 granted exploration permits for minerals covering an area of approximately 1,536 square kilometers located in Northern Queensland. ActivEX Limited was incorporated in 2005 and is based in Sydney, Australia.
